Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.45,0:01:18.66,English,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.74,0:01:20.91,English,,0,0,0,,You did a wonderful job. Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.99,0:01:23.37,English,,0,0,0,,Shh. Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.45,0:01:24.87,English,,0,0,0,,We did it, Pete. We did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.96,0:01:28.67,English,,0,0,0,,- For a moment, we had our doubts.\N- Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.75,0:01:32.17,English,,0,0,0,,To continue, you've listened\Nto a long and complex case...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.25,0:01:34.05,English,,0,0,0,,murder in the first degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.13,0:01:39.09,English,,0,0,0,,A premeditated murder is the most serious\Ncharge tried in our criminal courts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.18,0:01:40.93,English,,0,0,0,,You've listened to the testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.01,0:01:43.93,English,,0,0,0,,You've had the law read to you\Nand interpreted as it applies in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.02,0:01:48.02,English,,0,0,0,,It's now your duty to sit down and try\Nand separate the facts from the fancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.94,0:01:52.48,English,,0,0,0,,One man is dead.\NAnother man's life is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.28,0:01:57.28,English,,0,0,0,,If there's a reasonable doubt in your minds\Nas to the guilt of the accused...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.36,0:01:59.28,English,,0,0,0,,a reasonable doubt...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,then you must bring me\Na verdict of not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.24,0:02:04.12,English,,0,0,0,,Now if, however,\Nthere's no reasonable doubt...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.20,0:02:08.08,English,,0,0,0,,then you must in good conscience\Nfind the accused guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.21,0:02:13.34,English,,0,0,0,,However you decide,\Nyour verdict must be unanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.42,0:02:16.80,English,,0,0,0,,In the event\Nthat you find the accused guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.88,0:02:20.22,English,,0,0,0,,the bench will not entertain\Na recommendation for mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.30,0:02:23.51,English,,0,0,0,,The death sentence\Nis mandatory in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.60,0:02:27.31,English,,0,0,0,,You're faced with a grave responsibility.\NThank you, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.31,0:02:31.35,English,,0,0,0,,The alternate jurors are excused.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.36,0:02:39.36,English,,0,0,0,,The jury will now retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.36,0:04:39.36,English,,0,0,0,,Try this one. See if I can get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.69,0:04:42.44,English,,0,0,0,,It's a muggy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.70,0:04:48.07,English,,0,0,0,,Hey. Oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.13,0:05:02.21,English,,0,0,0,,- Piece of gum?\N- No, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:04.38,English,,0,0,0,,This thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.47,0:05:06.09,English,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- ...move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.72,0:05:09.89,English,,0,0,0,,- Come on, I'll give you a hand.\N- Give me a hand with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.97,0:05:11.31,English,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.94,0:05:18.56,English,,0,0,0,,- You know something?\N- Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:20.40,English,,0,0,0,,I called the weather bureau this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.48,0:05:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,This is gonna be\Nthe hottest day of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.48,0:05:24.07,English,,0,0,0,,Could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.15,0:05:26.07,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, you'd think they'd at least\Nair-condition these places.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.15,0:05:29.49,English,,0,0,0,,- What is your name, sir?\N- Oh, it's, uh - That one, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.57,0:05:30.99,English,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.08,0:05:33.83,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, gentlemen, everybody's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.91,0:05:36.75,English,,0,0,0,,Now, if there's anything you want,\NI'll be right outside the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.83,0:05:39.08,English,,0,0,0,,- Just knock.\N- Okay, thanks. We will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.60,0:05:52.81,English,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.89,0:05:54.35,English,,0,0,0,,I never knew they locked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.43,0:05:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,Sure they lock the door.\NWhat'd you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:06:00.10,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt just never occurred to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.73,0:06:03.52,English,,0,0,0,,What's that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.61,0:06:05.48,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, I thought we might want\Nto vote by ballot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.57,0:06:08.24,English,,0,0,0,,Great idea. Maybe we can\Nget him elected senator.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.49,0:06:12.24,English,,0,0,0,,Just in case, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.75,0:06:17.87,English,,0,0,0,,- Ηow'd you like it?\N- Oh, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.96,0:06:19.62,English,,0,0,0,,It was pretty interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:21.67,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah? I almost fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.75,0:06:24.34,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, I've never been\Non a jury before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.42,0:06:27.13,English,,0,0,0,,No? I've sat on many juries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.30,0:06:31.22,English,,0,0,0,,What gets me is the way\Nthose lawyers talk and talk and talk...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.30,0:06:33.47,English,,0,0,0,,even when it's an open-and-shut case\Nlike this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.56,0:06:35.26,English,,0,0,0,,Did you ever hear\Nso much talk about nothin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:37.22,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess they're entitled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.31,0:06:39.77,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. They're entitled.\NIt's the system, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.98,0:06:45.07,English,,0,0,0,,If you ask me, I'd slap those tough kids\Ndown before they start any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.15,0:06:47.23,English,,0,0,0,,It would save us a lot of time and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.32,0:06:48.86,English,,0,0,0,,- Hey, let's get started, huh?\N- That's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.95,0:06:51.57,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, let's get goin', huh?\N- We probably all got things to do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:54.70,English,,0,0,0,,I figured we'd start out with a five-minute break.\NThere's one gentleman in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.79,0:06:55.74,English,,0,0,0,,- Mr. Foreman.\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.83,0:06:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,- Are, uh - Are we gonna sit in order?\N- Gee, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.71,0:07:00.46,English,,0,0,0,,I, uh - Well, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.46,0:07:06.92,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, you're in my seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.01,0:07:09.01,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh. Excuse me.\N- That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.55,0:07:13.30,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's not a bad view, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.93,0:07:19.39,English,,0,0,0,,What did you think of the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.48,0:07:21.52,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, it had a lot of interest for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.60,0:07:24.73,English,,0,0,0,,No real... dead spots.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:28.07,English,,0,0,0,,I tell you, we were lucky\Nto get a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.15,0:07:30.11,English,,0,0,0,,I figured us for an assault or burglary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:32.45,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, they can be the dullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.03,0:07:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.41,0:07:36.99,English,,0,0,0,,That the Woolworth Building?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.08,0:07:38.99,English,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:40.66,English,,0,0,0,,Isn't that funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.75,0:07:43.12,English,,0,0,0,,You know, I've lived here all my life.\NI've never been inside that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.21,0:07:45.29,English,,0,0,0,,If you had to sort out all that junk...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:47.46,English,,0,0,0,,Like that thing with the movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.55,0:07:50.55,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. You can say that again.\N- And what about that business with the knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.63,0:07:53.51,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, asking grown-up people\Nto believe that kind of jazz, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.59,0:07:56.05,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I expected that.\NYou know what we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.14,0:07:58.60,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.68,0:08:00.39,English,,0,0,0,,Well, your horn works.\NNow try your lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:03.52,English,,0,0,0,,- What do you got, a cold?\N- And how.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.60,0:08:05.81,English,,0,0,0,,These hot-weather colds can kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.90,0:08:08.32,English,,0,0,0,,I can hardly touch my nose.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:11.94,English,,0,0,0,,I sure do. I just got over one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.03,0:08:14.78,English,,0,0,0,,Aw, come on. Mr.\NForeman, let's go here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.87,0:08:16.49,English,,0,0,0,,Well, that guy's still in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:19.41,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's new? I didn't get a chance\Nto see a paper this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.49,0:08:20.58,English,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.66,0:08:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,I was only wondering\Nhow the market closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:25.88,English,,0,0,0,,You got a seat on the Exchange?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:27.71,English,,0,0,0,,I'm a broker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.79,0:08:32.17,English,,0,0,0,,I run a messenger service -\Nthe Beck and Call Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.26,0:08:34.38,English,,0,0,0,,The name is my wife's idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.47,0:08:38.10,English,,0,0,0,,Got 37 men working.\NStarted with nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.18,0:08:41.35,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, men, let's take our seats, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.52,0:08:46.35,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we can all get outta here\Npretty quick, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.44,0:08:49.65,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know about the rest of you, but I happen\Nto have tickets to that ball game tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.73,0:08:51.57,English,,0,0,0,,Yanks and Cleveland.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.65,0:08:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we got this kid,\NModjelewski, in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.53,0:08:55.20,English,,0,0,0,,Ooh, he's a real bull, this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:08:57.41,English,,0,0,0,,You know - Phoom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.49,0:08:59.74,English,,0,0,0,,A real jug handle. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.83,0:09:02.08,English,,0,0,0,,Phoom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.16,0:09:04.50,English,,0,0,0,,You're a real baseball fan, aren't you?\NHuh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.58,0:09:06.04,English,,0,0,0,,Where do we sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.12,0:09:09.21,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought we'd sit in order,\Nyou know, by jury numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.29,0:09:11.71,English,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four, five -\Nso on, around the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:13.05,English,,0,0,0,,If that's okay with you gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:14.22,English,,0,0,0,,- Sure.\N- What's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.30,0:09:17.34,English,,0,0,0,,- I think it's reasonable to sit in order.\N- Let it be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.43,0:09:19.68,English,,0,0,0,,- Number 12. Do I sit down here?\N- Yeah. That's 12. We go around...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,- We start with you. One, right?\N- One, yeah. Two, three, four, five, six.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.10,0:09:25.43,English,,0,0,0,,What was your impression\Nof the prosecuting attorney?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.52,0:09:27.23,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Two. You're two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.31,0:09:28.48,English,,0,0,0,,I beg pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:32.73,English,,0,0,0,,I thought he was really sharp, the way\Nhe handled all those points one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.82,0:09:35.95,English,,0,0,0,,Logical sequence.\NI was very impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.03,0:09:39.03,English,,0,0,0,,I think he - he did an expert job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.12,0:09:42.12,English,,0,0,0,,A lot of drive too, you know?\NReal drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.20,0:09:44.29,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay, fellas, can we hold it down a minute?\N- Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, fellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.04,0:09:49.50,English,,0,0,0,,Say, we'd like to get started.\NGentleman at the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:53.34,English,,0,0,0,,- We'd like to get started.\N- Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.42,0:09:57.09,English,,0,0,0,,Pretty tough to figure, isn't it?\NKid kills his father - bing, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.18,0:09:59.76,English,,0,0,0,,Aw, listen, you analyze the figures,\Nyou'll see it happens all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.84,0:10:01.76,English,,0,0,0,,They let those kids\Nrun wild up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.85,0:10:04.56,English,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe it serves 'em right.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.64,0:10:06.23,English,,0,0,0,,Is - Is everyone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.31,0:10:08.14,English,,0,0,0,,The old man is inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.23,0:10:10.85,English,,0,0,0,,Oh. Would you, uh,\Nknock on the door for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.94,0:10:12.90,English,,0,0,0,,You a Yankee fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.98,0:10:14.53,English,,0,0,0,,No. Baltimore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.44,0:10:16.94,English,,0,0,0,,- Baltimore?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:20.78,English,,0,0,0,,That's like being hit in the head\Nwith a crowbar once a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.53,0:10:23.78,English,,0,0,0,,Who have they got?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:26.29,English,,0,0,0,,No, I mean, who have they got\Nbesides good groundskeepers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.37,0:10:27.91,English,,0,0,0,,Say, uh, we'd like to get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.00,0:10:31.04,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, forgive me, gentlemen.\NI - I didn't mean to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.84,0:10:33.63,English,,0,0,0,,Baltimore?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.71,0:10:36.51,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, gentlemen,\Nif I can have your attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.59,0:10:39.55,English,,0,0,0,,You fellas can handle this thing\Nany way that you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.63,0:10:42.14,English,,0,0,0,,I'm, um - You know,\NI'm not gonna make any rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.22,0:10:45.51,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, we can, well, discuss it first\Nand, uh, then vote on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.60,0:10:48.27,English,,0,0,0,,That's, of course, uh -\NThat's, uh, one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:51.31,English,,0,0,0,,And, uh, well, we can\Nvote on it right now, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:53.90,English,,0,0,0,,I think it's customary\Nto take a preliminary vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:57.57,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's - Let's vote. Who knows?\NMaybe we all can get outta here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:10:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.45,0:11:02.53,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, then I think that, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.62,0:11:05.49,English,,0,0,0,,Of course you know that we have\Na first-degree murder charge here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:07.66,English,,0,0,0,,and if we vote the accused guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.75,0:11:11.00,English,,0,0,0,,uh, we've got to send him\Nto the chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.08,0:11:14.84,English,,0,0,0,,- Um, that's mandatory.\N- I think we know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.92,0:11:16.67,English,,0,0,0,,- Let's see who's where.\N- We might as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.76,0:11:20.55,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay. Uh, anyone doesn't want to vote?\N- All right with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.76,0:11:26.35,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Then, uh, just remember that this\Nhas to be 12 to nothing either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.43,0:11:27.89,English,,0,0,0,,Um, that's the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.97,0:11:30.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, are we ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.10,0:11:33.10,English,,0,0,0,,Now, all those voting guilty,\Nplease raise your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.11,0:11:40.61,English,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four,\Nfive, six, seven...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:44.53,English,,0,0,0,,eight, nine, 10, 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.62,0:11:47.53,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. That's 11 guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.62,0:11:49.12,English,,0,0,0,,Those voting not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:52.37,English,,0,0,0,,One. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.46,0:11:54.75,English,,0,0,0,,That's 11 guilty. One not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:57.25,English,,0,0,0,,Well, now we know where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.34,0:12:01.51,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, oh, boy. There's always one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.05,0:12:04.34,English,,0,0,0,,So, what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.43,0:12:06.26,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess we talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.35,0:12:07.68,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.76,0:12:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,You really think he's innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:14.60,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.69,0:12:17.56,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, you sat in court with the rest of us.\NYou heard what we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.65,0:12:19.78,English,,0,0,0,,The kid's a dangerous killer.\NYou could see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.86,0:12:21.49,English,,0,0,0,,He's 18 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.57,0:12:23.65,English,,0,0,0,,Well, that's old enough. Ηe...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.74,0:12:26.41,English,,0,0,0,,He stabbed his own father\Nfour inches into the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.49,0:12:28.74,English,,0,0,0,,They proved it\Na dozen different ways in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:31.37,English,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to list them for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:32.75,English,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:34.92,English,,0,0,0,,Then what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.00,0:12:37.92,English,,0,0,0,,- I just want to talk.\N- What's there to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.00,0:12:39.34,English,,0,0,0,,Eleven men in here think he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.42,0:12:41.67,English,,0,0,0,,No one had to think about it twice\Nexcept you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:44.97,English,,0,0,0,,I want to ask you something.\NDo you believe his story?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:47.76,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know whether I believe it or not.\NMaybe I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:49.43,English,,0,0,0,,So how come you vote not guilty?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:51.43,English,,0,0,0,,Well, there were 11 votes for guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.52,0:12:54.27,English,,0,0,0,,It's not easy to raise my hand\Nand send a boy off to die...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.35,0:12:56.44,English,,0,0,0,,without talking about it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.52,0:12:58.94,English,,0,0,0,,- Well, now, who says it's easy?\N- No one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.23,0:13:02.40,English,,0,0,0,,What, just because I voted fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.49,0:13:04.90,English,,0,0,0,,I honestly think the guy's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.99,0:13:07.78,English,,0,0,0,,You couldn't change my mind\Nif you talked for a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.87,0:13:09.87,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not trying to change your mind.\NIt's just that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.45,0:13:12.70,English,,0,0,0,,We're talking about somebody's life here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.79,0:13:14.87,English,,0,0,0,,We can't decide it in five minutes.\NSupposing we're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.96,0:13:16.37,English,,0,0,0,,"Supposing we're wrong."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:18.46,English,,0,0,0,,Supposing this whole building\Nshould fall down on my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.54,0:13:20.54,English,,0,0,0,,- You can suppose anything.\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:23.13,English,,0,0,0,,Look, what's the difference\Nhow long it takes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.21,0:13:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,Suppose we do it in five minutes.\NSo what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.88,0:13:28.01,English,,0,0,0,,Let's take an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.09,0:13:30.01,English,,0,0,0,,The ball game doesn't start till 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.72,0:13:33.89,English,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.06,0:13:37.90,English,,0,0,0,,Who's got something to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.98,0:13:39.40,English,,0,0,0,,I'm willing to sit for an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:42.19,English,,0,0,0,,Great. I heard\Na pretty good story last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.28,0:13:44.36,English,,0,0,0,,That's not why we're sitting here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:48.61,English,,0,0,0,,All right, then you tell me.\NWhat are we sitting here for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:51.70,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Maybe no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,Look, this kid's been kicked around\Nall of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.25,0:14:00.17,English,,0,0,0,,you know, born in a slum,\Nmother dead since he was nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.25,0:14:02.46,English,,0,0,0,,He lived for a year and a half\Nin an orphanage when his...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.55,0:14:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,his father was serving a jail term\Nfor forgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.55,0:14:07.88,English,,0,0,0,,It's not a very happy beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.97,0:14:10.09,English,,0,0,0,,He's a - a wild, angry kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.18,0:14:11.89,English,,0,0,0,,That's all he's ever been.\NAnd you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.97,0:14:15.68,English,,0,0,0,,'Cause he's been hit on the head\Nby somebody once a day every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.77,0:14:17.98,English,,0,0,0,,He's had a -\NHe's had a pretty miserable 18 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.06,0:14:21.02,English,,0,0,0,,I - I just think we owe him a few words.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.11,0:14:24.65,English,,0,0,0,,I don't mind telling you this, mister.\NWe don't owe him a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.73,0:14:27.82,English,,0,0,0,,He got a fair trial, didn't he?\NWhat do you think that trial cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.90,0:14:30.99,English,,0,0,0,,- He's lucky he got it. You know what I mean?\N- You know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:33.41,English,,0,0,0,,Now, look, we're all grown-ups in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.49,0:14:35.37,English,,0,0,0,,We heard the facts, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.45,0:14:39.25,English,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna tell me that we're supposed\Nto believe this kid, knowing what he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.33,0:14:41.71,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, I've lived among them\Nall my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.79,0:14:45.13,English,,0,0,0,,You can't believe a word they say.\NYou know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.21,0:14:47.05,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, they're born liars.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.13,0:14:50.47,English,,0,0,0,,- Only an ignorant man can believe that.\N- Now listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.55,0:14:53.39,English,,0,0,0,,Do you think you were born\Nwith a monopoly on the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.47,0:14:56.06,English,,0,0,0,,I think certain things should be\Npointed out to this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.14,0:14:58.23,English,,0,0,0,,- Come on. This isn't Sunday.\N- We don't need a sermon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.31,0:15:00.56,English,,0,0,0,,- Come on.\N- We have a job to do. Now let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.60,0:15:04.65,English,,0,0,0,,Rice Pops.\NIt's a product I work on at the agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.48,0:15:08.11,English,,0,0,0,,"The breakfast with the built-in bounce."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.19,0:15:09.82,English,,0,0,0,,- I wrote that line.\N- Very catchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.90,0:15:12.07,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.\N- Say, do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.16,0:15:13.87,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.95,0:15:16.41,English,,0,0,0,,I have this habit of doodling.\NKeeps me thinking clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.49,0:15:18.20,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we have all this work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:20.00,English,,0,0,0,,- There's no point staying here forever.\N- Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:22.29,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.38,0:15:26.17,English,,0,0,0,,perhaps if the gentleman down there\Nwho's disagreeing with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.25,0:15:29.55,English,,0,0,0,,Well, perhaps you could tell us why.\NYou know, let us know what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.63,0:15:32.01,English,,0,0,0,,And we might be able to show you\Nwhere you're mixed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.09,0:15:33.76,English,,0,0,0,,Well, look, maybe -\NMaybe this is an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.85,0:15:36.26,English,,0,0,0,,Now, I haven't given it much thought,\Nbut it seems to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.35,0:15:40.77,English,,0,0,0,,that it's up to the group of us to convince\Nthis gentleman that he's wrong and we're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.85,0:15:43.40,English,,0,0,0,,Now, maybe if we each took\Na couple of minutes just to...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.81,0:15:46.23,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it was just a quick idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.32,0:15:47.77,English,,0,0,0,,No, no, no. That's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.86,0:15:50.94,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, suppose we go\Nonce around the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:53.91,English,,0,0,0,,- I guess you're first.\N- Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.99,0:15:55.32,English,,0,0,0,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.87,0:15:59.29,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it-it's hard to put into words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.33,0:16:02.33,English,,0,0,0,,I just think he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.42,0:16:04.92,English,,0,0,0,,I thought it was obvious\Nfrom the word go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.00,0:16:06.50,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, nobody proved otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.59,0:16:08.13,English,,0,0,0,,Nobody has to prove otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:10.46,English,,0,0,0,,The burden of proof's on the prosecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.55,0:16:13.01,English,,0,0,0,,The defendant doesn't even\Nhave to open his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.09,0:16:16.22,English,,0,0,0,,- That's in the Constitution.\N- Oh, well, sure, I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.30,0:16:18.26,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, what I meant was, is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.06,0:16:22.06,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I just think he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.14,0:16:23.85,English,,0,0,0,,I-I mean, somebody saw him do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.94,0:16:28.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Uh, here's what I think,\Nand I have no personal feelings about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.07,0:16:31.23,English,,0,0,0,,I just want to talk about facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.24,0:16:34.36,English,,0,0,0,,Number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:39.03,English,,0,0,0,,The old man lived downstairs under the room\Nwhere the killing took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:41.24,English,,0,0,0,,At 10 minutes after 12:00\Non the night of the killing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.33,0:16:45.00,English,,0,0,0,,he heard loud noises,\Nsaid it sounded like a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.08,0:16:47.96,English,,0,0,0,,And he heard the kid yell out,\N"I'm gonna kill ya."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.04,0:16:50.34,English,,0,0,0,,A second later,\Nhe heard a body hit the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.42,0:16:52.13,English,,0,0,0,,Ran to the door, opened it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.22,0:16:54.63,English,,0,0,0,,saw the kid running down the stairs\Nand out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.72,0:16:56.01,English,,0,0,0,,Called the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.09,0:16:58.76,English,,0,0,0,,They came in, found the old man\Nwith a knife in his chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:02.10,English,,0,0,0,,The coroner fixed the time of death\Naround midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.18,0:17:05.27,English,,0,0,0,,Now these are facts.\NYou can't refute facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.35,0:17:07.52,English,,0,0,0,,The kid is guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.61,0:17:09.61,English,,0,0,0,,I'm just as sentimental as the next fella.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.69,0:17:13.57,English,,0,0,0,,I know he's only 18, but he's still\Ngotta pay for what he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.65,0:17:15.11,English,,0,0,0,,I'm with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.20,0:17:17.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Are you finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.82,0:17:19.28,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.\N- Right. Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.37,0:17:22.58,English,,0,0,0,,It is obvious, to me anyway,\Nthat the boy's entire story was flimsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.66,0:17:24.87,English,,0,0,0,,He claimed he was at the movies\Nduring the time of the killing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.96,0:17:27.50,English,,0,0,0,,and yet, one hour later, he couldn't\Nremember the names of the films he saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.58,0:17:29.42,English,,0,0,0,,- or who played in them.\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:31.80,English,,0,0,0,,And no one saw him going in\Nor out of the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.88,0:17:33.51,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, what about the woman\Nacross the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.59,0:17:35.88,English,,0,0,0,,If her testimony don't prove it,\Nnothing does.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.97,0:17:38.30,English,,0,0,0,,That's right. She was the one\Nwho actually saw the killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.39,0:17:40.80,English,,0,0,0,,- Now, fellas, please.\N- Let's go in order here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.89,0:17:44.14,English,,0,0,0,,Just a minute. Here's a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.23,0:17:46.69,English,,0,0,0,,Here's a woman who was lying in bed.\NShe can't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.77,0:17:48.69,English,,0,0,0,,She's dying with the heat.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.77,0:17:50.61,English,,0,0,0,,Anyway, she looks out the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.69,0:17:54.28,English,,0,0,0,,and right across the street she sees\Nthe kid stick the knife into his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.36,0:17:57.24,English,,0,0,0,,The time is 12:10 on the nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.32,0:17:59.20,English,,0,0,0,,Everything fits.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.28,0:18:01.12,English,,0,0,0,,Look, she's known the kid all his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:03.33,English,,0,0,0,,His window is right opposite hers\Nacross the el tracks...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.41,0:18:05.08,English,,0,0,0,,and she swore she saw him do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:07.83,English,,0,0,0,,- Through the windows of the passing el train.\N- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.92,0:18:12.09,English,,0,0,0,,This el train had no passengers on it.\NIt was just being moved downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:15.09,English,,0,0,0,,The lights were out, remember?\NAnd they proved in court that, at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.17,0:18:17.59,English,,0,0,0,,you can look through the windows\Nof an el train when the lights are out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.68,0:18:20.01,English,,0,0,0,,and see what's happening\Non the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.09,0:18:22.93,English,,0,0,0,,- They proved it.\N- I'd like to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.01,0:18:25.68,English,,0,0,0,,You don't believe the boy's story.\NHow come you believe the woman's?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.77,0:18:27.52,English,,0,0,0,,She's one of them too, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.19,0:18:32.19,English,,0,0,0,,You're a pretty smart fella, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.27,0:18:33.69,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay, gentlemen.\N- Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.78,0:18:35.98,English,,0,0,0,,- Now, gentlemen.\N- Come on. Sit down. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.07,0:18:38.61,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's he so wise about?\NI'm telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:41.95,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay, now come on.\N- Now we're not gonna get anywhere fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.03,0:18:43.28,English,,0,0,0,,Whose turn is it next?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.37,0:18:46.20,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh, his. Number five.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.46,0:18:51.21,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, may I - Can I pass? It...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.00,0:18:54.04,English,,0,0,0,,Well, uh, that's your privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.13,0:18:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, how about the next gentleman?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.34,0:19:00.01,English,,0,0,0,,Oh. Well, uh, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.09,0:19:04.30,English,,0,0,0,,I started to be convinced, you know,\Nvery early in the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.89,0:19:09.02,English,,0,0,0,,You see, I was looking for a motive.\NThat's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.10,0:19:13.31,English,,0,0,0,,Because if you don't have a motive,\Nwhere's your case, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.40,0:19:16.48,English,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that, uh, testimony\Nfrom those people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.57,0:19:19.61,English,,0,0,0,,in the apartment across the hall\Nfrom the kid's apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.70,0:19:21.95,English,,0,0,0,,that was very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.03,0:19:24.83,English,,0,0,0,,Didn't they say something about a -\Na fight and an argument...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.91,0:19:29.33,English,,0,0,0,,between the old man and his son\Naround about, uh, 7:00 that night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.41,0:19:31.87,English,,0,0,0,,- I mean, I could be wrong, but I -\N- It was 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:34.00,English,,0,0,0,,It was 8:00. That's right.\NThey heard an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.09,0:19:35.84,English,,0,0,0,,They couldn't hear what it was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.92,0:19:37.88,English,,0,0,0,,Then they heard\Nthe father hit the boy twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:40.92,English,,0,0,0,,Finally they saw the boy\Nrun angrily out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.01,0:19:42.59,English,,0,0,0,,What does that prove?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.68,0:19:46.35,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it don't exactly prove anything.\NIt's just part of the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:49.35,English,,0,0,0,,Well, you said it provided a motive.\NThe prosecuting attorney said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.43,0:19:51.69,English,,0,0,0,,I don't think\Nthat was a very strong motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.77,0:19:55.36,English,,0,0,0,,This boy's been hit so many times in his\Nlife that violence is practically a...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.44,0:19:57.82,English,,0,0,0,,It's a normal state of affairs with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.90,0:20:02.11,English,,0,0,0,,I just - I can't see two slaps in the face\Nprovoking him into committing murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:05.78,English,,0,0,0,,It may have been two too many.\NEveryone has a breaking point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.33,0:20:10.41,English,,0,0,0,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.50,0:20:12.96,English,,0,0,0,,- No.\N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.04,0:20:14.79,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, how about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.63,0:20:18.59,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. It's all been said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.13,0:20:22.76,English,,0,0,0,,You can talk here forever.\NIt's still the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.97,0:20:26.93,English,,0,0,0,,This kid is five for 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.01,0:20:28.89,English,,0,0,0,,Well, look at his record.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.97,0:20:31.18,English,,0,0,0,,When he was 10,\Nhe was in children's court.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.27,0:20:33.06,English,,0,0,0,,He threw a rock at a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.14,0:20:35.44,English,,0,0,0,,When he was 15, he was in reform school.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,He stole a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.44,0:20:39.94,English,,0,0,0,,He's been arrested for mugging.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.03,0:20:42.03,English,,0,0,0,,He was picked up twice for knife fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.11,0:20:44.20,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, they say\Nhe's real handy with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.28,0:20:47.07,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is a very fine boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:50.16,English,,0,0,0,,Ever since he was five years old,\Nhis father beat him up regularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.24,0:20:52.66,English,,0,0,0,,- He used his fists.\N- Well, so would I.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.75,0:20:54.25,English,,0,0,0,,A kid like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.33,0:20:57.50,English,,0,0,0,,It's these kids, the way they are nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.00,0:21:03.17,English,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid,\NI used to call my father "sir."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.93,0:21:05.22,English,,0,0,0,,That's right. "Sir."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.30,0:21:07.26,English,,0,0,0,,Do you ever hear a kid\Ncall his father that any more?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.35,0:21:09.85,English,,0,0,0,,Fathers don't seem to think\Nit's important any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.64,0:21:12.68,English,,0,0,0,,- You got any kids?\N- Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.06,0:21:15.39,English,,0,0,0,,I got one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.90,0:21:18.65,English,,0,0,0,,Twenty-two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.78,0:21:27.53,English,,0,0,0,,When he was nine years old,\Nhe ran away from a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.24,0:21:32.41,English,,0,0,0,,I saw it. I was so embarrassed\NI almost threw up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.08,0:21:38.71,English,,0,0,0,,I said, "I'm gonna make a man out of you\Nif I have to break you in two trying."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.21,0:21:43.13,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I made a man out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.13,0:21:46.30,English,,0,0,0,,When he was 16, we had a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.89,0:21:50.26,English,,0,0,0,,Hit me in the jaw.\NHe was a big kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.68,0:21:55.77,English,,0,0,0,,Haven't seen him for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.69,0:21:59.98,English,,0,0,0,,Kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.69,0:22:03.65,English,,0,0,0,,Work your heart out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.24,0:22:07.49,English,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.57,0:22:09.91,English,,0,0,0,,I think we're missing the point here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.99,0:22:13.41,English,,0,0,0,,This boy, let's say he's the product\Nof a broken home and a filthy neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.49,0:22:17.08,English,,0,0,0,,We can't help that. We're here to decide\Nwhether he's innocent or guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.16,0:22:20.08,English,,0,0,0,,not to go into the reasons\Nwhy he grew up the way he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.17,0:22:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,He was born in a slum.\NSlums are breeding grounds for criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.96,0:22:24.84,English,,0,0,0,,I know it, and so do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.92,0:22:29.63,English,,0,0,0,,It's no secret children from slum backgrounds\Nare potential menaces to society.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.72,0:22:31.89,English,,0,0,0,,- Now I think -\N- Brother, you can say that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.97,0:22:34.51,English,,0,0,0,,The kids who crawl out of these places\Nare real trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.60,0:22:36.85,English,,0,0,0,,- I don't want any part of them. I'm telling you.\N- Listen, mister. Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.93,0:22:40.65,English,,0,0,0,,- I, uh - I've lived in a slum all my life.\N- Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.73,0:22:44.15,English,,0,0,0,,Please, I - I played in backyards\Nthat were filled with garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.23,0:22:46.28,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, maybe you can still\Nsmell it on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.36,0:22:47.69,English,,0,0,0,,Now, listen, sonny.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.78,0:22:49.36,English,,0,0,0,,- Come on now.\N- There's nothing personal about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.45,0:22:51.99,English,,0,0,0,,- No, there was something personal.\N- Aw, come on, fella. He didn't mean you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.07,0:22:54.16,English,,0,0,0,,Let's not be so sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.24,0:22:56.08,English,,0,0,0,,This sensitivity I can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.16,0:23:00.79,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, look, let's stop the arguing.\NWe're only wasting time, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.96,0:23:04.09,English,,0,0,0,,Look, your turn down there.\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.42,0:23:08.26,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't expect a turn. I thought\Nyou were all gonna try to convince me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.34,0:23:10.09,English,,0,0,0,,- Wasn't that the idea?\N- Check. That was the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.18,0:23:12.39,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh, I forgot about that. He's right.\N- What difference does it make?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.47,0:23:14.80,English,,0,0,0,,He's the one who's keeping us in here.\NLet's hear what he's got to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.89,0:23:17.60,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, now wait a minute.\NWe decided to do this a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.68,0:23:19.31,English,,0,0,0,,I think we ought to stick to that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.39,0:23:21.39,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, stop being a kid, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.48,0:23:23.48,English,,0,0,0,,- What do you mean "a kid"?\N- What do you think I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.56,0:23:25.19,English,,0,0,0,,K-I-D. Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.78,0:23:31.45,English,,0,0,0,,What? Listen, just because I'm trying\Nto keep this thing organized?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.53,0:23:33.66,English,,0,0,0,,Here, you take it.\NYou take on the responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.74,0:23:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,I'll just - I'll keep my mouth shut.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.70,0:23:37.70,English,,0,0,0,,What are you getting so hot about?\NCalm down, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.79,0:23:39.12,English,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me to calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.21,0:23:41.33,English,,0,0,0,,Here. You wanna take the chair,\Njust take the chair. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.42,0:23:43.88,English,,0,0,0,,- Did you ever see such a thing?\N- See if you can keep it running.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.96,0:23:45.92,English,,0,0,0,,- Listen, you think it's funny or something?\N- Hey, forget it, fella.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.00,0:23:47.59,English,,0,0,0,,The whole thing's unimportant.\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.67,0:23:50.80,English,,0,0,0,,- Unimportant? Oh, here, you try it.\N- No, nobody wants to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.88,0:23:52.63,English,,0,0,0,,You're doing a beautiful job.\NSit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.72,0:23:55.55,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're doing great.\NJust great, fella.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.64,0:23:57.51,English,,0,0,0,,You stay in there and pitch. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.47,0:24:00.68,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's hear from somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.19,0:24:06.27,English,,0,0,0,,Well, if you want me to tell you how I\Nfeel about it, it's all right with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.36,0:24:08.48,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, I don't care what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.57,0:24:11.44,English,,0,0,0,,All right, I don't have anything brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.53,0:24:13.66,English,,0,0,0,,I only know as much as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.74,0:24:17.49,English,,0,0,0,,According to the testimony,\Nthe boy looks guilty. Maybe he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.58,0:24:21.75,English,,0,0,0,,I sat there in court for six days\Nlistening while the evidence built up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.37,0:24:24.08,English,,0,0,0,,Everybody sounded so positive, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.17,0:24:26.63,English,,0,0,0,,I-I began to get a peculiar feeling\Nabout this trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.71,0:24:28.80,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, nothing is that positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.88,0:24:31.01,English,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of questions\NI'd have liked to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.09,0:24:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Maybe they wouldn't\Nhave meant anything, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.88,0:24:35.84,English,,0,0,0,,I began to get the feeling\Nthat the defense counsel...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.93,0:24:38.43,English,,0,0,0,,wasn't conducting a thorough-enough\Ncross-examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.51,0:24:41.89,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, he - he let too many things go by,\Nlittle things that...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.98,0:24:44.73,English,,0,0,0,,What little things? Listen,\Nwhen these fellas don't ask questions...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.81,0:24:47.31,English,,0,0,0,,it's because they know the answers already\Nand they figure they'll be hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.40,0:24:51.32,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's also possible for a lawyer\Nto be just plain stupid, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.40,0:24:52.69,English,,0,0,0,,I mean it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.78,0:24:54.45,English,,0,0,0,,You sound like you met\Nmy brother-in-law once.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.53,0:25:00.24,English,,0,0,0,,I - I kept putting myself\Nin the kid's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.08,0:25:04.21,English,,0,0,0,,I'd have asked for another lawyer, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.29,0:25:06.83,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, if I was on trial for my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.92,0:25:11.71,English,,0,0,0,,I'd want my lawyer to tear the prosecution\Nwitnesses to shreds, or at least try to.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.80,0:25:15.76,English,,0,0,0,,Look, there was one alleged eyewitness\Nto this killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.30,0:25:19.68,English,,0,0,0,,Someone else claims he heard the killing,\Nsaw the boy run out afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.76,0:25:21.89,English,,0,0,0,,And there was a lot\Nof circumstantial evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.97,0:25:25.48,English,,0,0,0,,But actually, those two witnesses\Nwere the entire case for the prosecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.56,0:25:27.35,English,,0,0,0,,Supposing they're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.44,0:25:29.23,English,,0,0,0,,What do you mean\Nsupposing they're wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.32,0:25:31.19,English,,0,0,0,,What's the point\Nof having witnesses at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.28,0:25:33.90,English,,0,0,0,,- Could they be wrong?\N- What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.99,0:25:35.53,English,,0,0,0,,Those people sat on the stand under oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.61,0:25:37.16,English,,0,0,0,,They're only people.\NPeople make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.24,0:25:38.95,English,,0,0,0,,Could they be wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.74,0:25:42.66,English,,0,0,0,,- Well, no, I don't think so.\N- Do you know so?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.75,0:25:44.58,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on.\NNobody can know a thing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.66,0:25:46.37,English,,0,0,0,,This isn't an exact science.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.46,0:25:47.79,English,,0,0,0,,That's right. It isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.96,0:25:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, let - Let's get to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.80,0:25:58.38,English,,0,0,0,,What about the switch knife\Nthey found in the old man's chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.47,0:26:00.89,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, wait-wait a minute.\NThere's some people who haven't talked yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.97,0:26:02.97,English,,0,0,0,,- Shouldn't we go in order?\N- They'll get a chance to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.06,0:26:05.39,English,,0,0,0,,Be quiet a second, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.48,0:26:06.77,English,,0,0,0,,What about it, this...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.85,0:26:10.31,English,,0,0,0,,the knife this fine upright boy\Nadmitted buying the night of the killing?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.40,0:26:11.73,English,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.82,0:26:14.07,English,,0,0,0,,All right, let's talk about it.\NLet's get it in here and look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.15,0:26:15.90,English,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see it again.\NMr. Foreman?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.99,0:26:19.07,English,,0,0,0,,- We all saw what it looks like.\N- Why do we have to see it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.16,0:26:21.12,English,,0,0,0,,The gentleman has a right\Nto see exhibits in evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.33,0:26:24.79,English,,0,0,0,,Say, could you bring us the knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.87,0:26:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,- Knife?\N- Yeah. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.33,0:26:31.58,English,,0,0,0,,The knife and the way it was bought\Nis pretty strong evidence, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.67,0:26:33.34,English,,0,0,0,,- I do.\N- Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.42,0:26:35.92,English,,0,0,0,,Now, suppose we take these facts\None at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.01,0:26:39.26,English,,0,0,0,,One. The boy admitted going out of the house\Nat 8:00 on the night of the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.34,0:26:41.26,English,,0,0,0,,after being slapped several times\Nby his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.35,0:26:44.10,English,,0,0,0,,No, no. No, he didn't say "slapped."\NHe said "punched."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.18,0:26:46.60,English,,0,0,0,,There's a difference\Nbetween a slap and a punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.68,0:26:49.27,English,,0,0,0,,After being hit several times\Nby his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.35,0:26:51.60,English,,0,0,0,,Two. He went directly\Nto a neighborhood junk shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.69,0:26:53.82,English,,0,0,0,,- where he bought one of those -\N- Switch knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.90,0:26:55.90,English,,0,0,0,,Switchblade knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.99,0:26:57.78,English,,0,0,0,,This wasn't what you'd call\Nan ordinary knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.86,0:27:00.36,English,,0,0,0,,It had a very unusual carved handle\Nand blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.45,0:27:01.95,English,,0,0,0,,The storekeeper who sold it to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.03,0:27:05.16,English,,0,0,0,,said it was the only one of its kind\Nhe had ever had in stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.24,0:27:09.00,English,,0,0,0,,Three. He met some friends of his\Nin front of a tavern about 8:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.08,0:27:10.58,English,,0,0,0,,Am I right so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.67,0:27:12.79,English,,0,0,0,,- Yes, you are.\N- You bet he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.88,0:27:16.05,English,,0,0,0,,He talked with his friends for about\Nan hour, leaving them at 9:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.13,0:27:19.09,English,,0,0,0,,During this time,\Nthey saw the switch knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.17,0:27:20.97,English,,0,0,0,,Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.05,0:27:23.47,English,,0,0,0,,They identified the death weapon\Nin court...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.55,0:27:26.06,English,,0,0,0,,as that very same knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.14,0:27:28.93,English,,0,0,0,,Five. Ηe arrived home at about 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.02,0:27:31.35,English,,0,0,0,,Now this is where the stories\Noffered by the State and the boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.44,0:27:33.35,English,,0,0,0,,begin to diverge slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.44,0:27:36.02,English,,0,0,0,,He claims that he went to a movie\Nat about 11:30...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.11,0:27:40.15,English,,0,0,0,,returning home at 3:10 to find his\Nfather dead and himself arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.24,0:27:42.28,English,,0,0,0,,He also claims that\Nthe two detectives who arrested him...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.36,0:27:44.66,English,,0,0,0,,threw him down a half a flight of stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.74,0:27:46.58,English,,0,0,0,,Now, what happened to the switch knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.66,0:27:49.29,English,,0,0,0,,He claims that it fell through a hole\Nin his pocket on the way to the movies...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.37,0:27:54.04,English,,0,0,0,,sometime between 11:30 and 3:10\Nand that he never saw it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.13,0:27:56.09,English,,0,0,0,,Now there's a tale, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.17,0:27:59.67,English,,0,0,0,,I think it's quite clear that the boy\Nnever went to the movies that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.76,0:28:01.72,English,,0,0,0,,No one in the house\Nsaw him go out at 11:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.80,0:28:03.30,English,,0,0,0,,No one at the theater identified him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.39,0:28:05.51,English,,0,0,0,,He couldn't even remember\Nthe names of the pictures he saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.56,0:28:10.27,English,,0,0,0,,- What actually happened is this.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.35,0:28:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,The boy stayed home,\Nhad another fight with his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.65,0:28:17.36,English,,0,0,0,,stabbed him to death and left the\Nhouse at 10 minutes after 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.44,0:28:20.19,English,,0,0,0,,He even remembered to wipe the knife\Nclean of fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.28,0:28:22.90,English,,0,0,0,,Now are you trying to tell me\Nthat this knife...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.99,0:28:24.91,English,,0,0,0,,really fell through a hole\Nin the boy's pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.99,0:28:27.37,English,,0,0,0,,someone picked it up off the street,\Nwent to the boy's house...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.45,0:28:30.12,English,,0,0,0,,and stabbed his father with it\Njust to test its sharpness?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.20,0:28:32.21,English,,0,0,0,,No. I'm just saying it's possible\Nthe boy lost his knife...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.29,0:28:34.50,English,,0,0,0,,and that somebody else stabbed his father\Nwith a similar knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.58,0:28:35.79,English,,0,0,0,,It's just possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.88,0:28:37.46,English,,0,0,0,,Take a look at this knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.38,0:28:41.59,English,,0,0,0,,It's a very unusual knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.67,0:28:43.22,English,,0,0,0,,I've never seen one like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.30,0:28:46.09,English,,0,0,0,,Neither had the storekeeper\Nwho sold it to the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.18,0:28:49.14,English,,0,0,0,,Aren't you asking us to accept\Na pretty incredible coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.22,0:28:51.56,English,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying a coincidence is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.64,0:28:53.14,English,,0,0,0,,And I say it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.78,0:29:01.48,English,,0,0,0,,Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.57,0:29:02.94,English,,0,0,0,,- Where'd you get that?\N- It's the same knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.03,0:29:04.53,English,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.61,0:29:06.24,English,,0,0,0,,Where did you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.32,0:29:08.57,English,,0,0,0,,I went out walking\Nfor a couple of hours last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.66,0:29:10.66,English,,0,0,0,,I walked through the boy's neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.74,0:29:13.75,English,,0,0,0,,I bought that at a little pawnshop\Njust two blocks from the boy's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.83,0:29:15.29,English,,0,0,0,,It cost six dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.37,0:29:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,It's against the law\Nto buy or sell switchblade knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.59,0:29:20.84,English,,0,0,0,,That's right. I broke the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.92,0:29:24.92,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, you pulled a real bright trick.\NNow, supposing you tell me what it proves.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.01,0:29:27.09,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe there are 10 knives like that.\NSo what?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.18,0:29:29.97,English,,0,0,0,,- Maybe there are.\N- Well, what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.06,0:29:33.35,English,,0,0,0,,You found another knife like it.\NWhat's that, the discovery of the age or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.43,0:29:35.77,English,,0,0,0,,You mean you're asking us to believe\Nthat somebody else did the stabbing...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.85,0:29:37.65,English,,0,0,0,,with exactly the same kind of knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.73,0:29:38.98,English,,0,0,0,,The odds are a million-to-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.06,0:29:41.77,English,,0,0,0,,- It's possible.\N- But not very probable.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.99,0:29:44.99,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, fellas, let's take our seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.07,0:29:46.70,English,,0,0,0,,There's no point in standing around\Nall over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.74,0:29:52.16,English,,0,0,0,,You know, it's interesting that he'd find a\Nknife exactly like the one the boy bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.24,0:29:55.00,English,,0,0,0,,What's interesting about it?\N"Interesting."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.08,0:29:56.96,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know.\NI just thought it was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.04,0:29:58.83,English,,0,0,0,,There are still 11 of us here\Nwho think he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.92,0:30:01.21,English,,0,0,0,,- Right.\N- What do you think you're gonna accomplish?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.30,0:30:03.13,English,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna change anybody's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.21,0:30:05.59,English,,0,0,0,,So if you wanna be stubborn\Nand hang this jury, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.67,0:30:08.72,English,,0,0,0,,The kid will be tried again\Nand found guilty sure as he's born.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.26,0:30:12.14,English,,0,0,0,,That's probably right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.22,0:30:15.43,English,,0,0,0,,So what are you gonna do?\NYou know, we could be here all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.52,0:30:18.77,English,,0,0,0,,It's only one night. A boy may die.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.85,0:30:21.40,English,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we just\Nset up house here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.48,0:30:23.94,English,,0,0,0,,Someone send for Potsy the policeman\Nand get a pinochle deck...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.03,0:30:26.53,English,,0,0,0,,and, uh, we'll just\Nsweat the whole thing out right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.03,0:30:31.07,English,,0,0,0,,- I don't think he ought to joke about it.\N- What do you want me to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.16,0:30:34.83,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, listen! I don't see what all this stuff\Nabout the knife's got to do with anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.91,0:30:37.83,English,,0,0,0,,Somebody saw the kid stab his father.\NWhat more do we need?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.92,0:30:40.71,English,,0,0,0,,You guys can talk the ears right off my head.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.79,0:30:43.50,English,,0,0,0,,I got three garages of mine goin' to pot\Nwhile you're talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.59,0:30:45.25,English,,0,0,0,,So let's get done and get outta here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.34,0:30:48.76,English,,0,0,0,,The knife was very important to the\Ndistrict attorney. He spent a whole day...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.84,0:30:51.30,English,,0,0,0,,He's a 15th assistant or something.\NWhat does he know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.39,0:30:52.85,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's hold it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.93,0:30:55.26,English,,0,0,0,,These side arguments\Nare only slowing us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.14,0:30:59.52,English,,0,0,0,,Well, what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.60,0:31:01.10,English,,0,0,0,,You're the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.03,0:31:11.07,English,,0,0,0,,I have a proposition\Nto make to all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.16,0:31:13.91,English,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna call for another vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.37,0:31:20.58,English,,0,0,0,,I want you 11 men to vote\Nby secret written ballot.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.67,0:31:22.71,English,,0,0,0,,I'll abstain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.79,0:31:25.59,English,,0,0,0,,If there are 11 votes for guilty,\NI won't stand alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.67,0:31:29.47,English,,0,0,0,,We'll take in a guilty verdict\Nto the judge right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.93,0:31:34.64,English,,0,0,0,,But if anyone votes not guilty,\Nwe stay here and talk it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.98,0:31:40.89,English,,0,0,0,,Well, that's it.\NIf you want to try it, I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.98,0:31:42.44,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's do it the hard way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.52,0:31:44.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, that sounds fair.\NEveryone agreed?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.52,0:31:46.61,English,,0,0,0,,- Anyone doesn't agree?\N- Fine, fine. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.69,0:31:47.73,English,,0,0,0,,Here, pass these along.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.82,0:31:49.57,English,,0,0,0,,Is that the right time?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.64,0:32:47.46,English,,0,0,0,,"Guilty."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.55,0:32:54.18,English,,0,0,0,,"Not guilty."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.26,0:32:55.68,English,,0,0,0,,"Guilty."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.76,0:32:57.43,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, how do you like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.51,0:32:59.97,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, and another chap flaps his wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.06,0:33:02.81,English,,0,0,0,,All right, who was it?\NCome on. I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.89,0:33:05.14,English,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. This was a secret ballot.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.23,0:33:06.77,English,,0,0,0,,We all agreed on that, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.86,0:33:08.98,English,,0,0,0,,If the gentleman wanted\Nto remain secret...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.07,0:33:10.94,English,,0,0,0,,Secret? What do you mean secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.03,0:33:14.24,English,,0,0,0,,There are no secrets in a jury room.\NI know who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.99,0:33:16.91,English,,0,0,0,,Brother, you really are something.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.99,0:33:18.99,English,,0,0,0,,You sit here, vote guilty\Nlike the rest of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.08,0:33:22.37,English,,0,0,0,,and then some golden-voiced preacher\Nstarts tearin' your poor heart out...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.45,0:33:25.75,English,,0,0,0,,about some underprivileged kid\Njust couldn't help becomin' a murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.83,0:33:27.33,English,,0,0,0,,and you change your vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.42,0:33:29.54,English,,0,0,0,,If that isn't the most sick...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.63,0:33:33.30,English,,0,0,0,,Why don't you drop a quarter\Nin his collection box?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.38,0:33:35.34,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, now just wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.43,0:33:37.01,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, you can't talk to me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.09,0:33:38.93,English,,0,0,0,,- No. Who do you think you are?\N- Calm down. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.01,0:33:41.35,English,,0,0,0,,No. Who does he think he is?\NDid you hear him?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.43,0:33:44.89,English,,0,0,0,,- It doesn't matter. He's very excitable. Sit down.\N- Excitable? You bet I'm excitable!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.98,0:33:47.81,English,,0,0,0,,We're trying to put a guilty man\Nin the chair where he belongs!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.90,0:33:50.56,English,,0,0,0,,Someone starts telling us fairy tales,\Nand we're listenin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.65,0:33:52.40,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, uh, come on, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.48,0:33:54.40,English,,0,0,0,,What made you change your vote?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.49,0:33:56.11,English,,0,0,0,,He didn't change his vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.20,0:33:57.36,English,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.45,0:33:59.41,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh, fine.\N- I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.49,0:34:01.45,English,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to tell you why?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.54,0:34:03.41,English,,0,0,0,,No, I wouldn't like you to tell me why.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.50,0:34:06.04,English,,0,0,0,,I'd like to make it clear anyway,\Nif you don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.12,0:34:07.62,English,,0,0,0,,Do we have to listen to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.71,0:34:09.46,English,,0,0,0,,The man wants to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.54,0:34:11.13,English,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.21,0:34:14.55,English,,0,0,0,,This gentleman has been\Nstanding alone against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.63,0:34:16.88,English,,0,0,0,,Now, he doesn't say\Nthe boy is not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.97,0:34:18.93,English,,0,0,0,,He just isn't sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.01,0:34:21.85,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not easy to stand alone\Nagainst the ridicule of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.93,0:34:25.06,English,,0,0,0,,So he gambled for support,\Nand I gave it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.14,0:34:26.85,English,,0,0,0,,I respect his motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.94,0:34:31.48,English,,0,0,0,,The boy on trial is probably guilty,\Nbut, uh, I want to hear more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.57,0:34:33.36,English,,0,0,0,,Right now, the vote is 10 to two.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.44,0:34:35.69,English,,0,0,0,,I'm talking here!\NYou have no right to leave this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.78,0:34:37.65,English,,0,0,0,,He can't hear you. He never will.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.74,0:34:39.32,English,,0,0,0,,Let's sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.49,0:34:45.70,English,,0,0,0,,Shall we continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.79,0:34:48.00,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I - I think we ought\Nto take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.08,0:34:52.21,English,,0,0,0,,You know, one man's inside,\Nand I think we ought to wait for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.29,0:34:55.25,English,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.34,0:34:57.09,English,,0,0,0,,Looks like we're really\Nhung up here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.47,0:35:00.80,English,,0,0,0,,And that thing with the old man,\Nthat was pretty unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.89,0:35:05.35,English,,0,0,0,,I wish I could figure out some way\Nwe could break it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.48,0:35:11.94,English,,0,0,0,,You know, in advertising -\NI told you I worked in an agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.02,0:35:13.02,English,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.11,0:35:15.11,English,,0,0,0,,Well, there's some pretty strange people\Nworking there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.19,0:35:17.28,English,,0,0,0,,Well, they're not strange really, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.36,0:35:19.99,English,,0,0,0,,It's just that they have peculiar ways\Nof expressing themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.07,0:35:21.32,English,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.41,0:35:23.62,English,,0,0,0,,Of course, I suppose it's the same\Nin your business too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.37,0:35:25.87,English,,0,0,0,,What do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.95,0:35:28.12,English,,0,0,0,,- I'm a watchmaker.\N- Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.21,0:35:31.42,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I imagine the finest watchmakers\Nin the world come from Europe, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.50,0:35:34.50,English,,0,0,0,,Anyway, as I was telling you, in an\Nagency, when we reach a point like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.59,0:35:38.09,English,,0,0,0,,I'm telling him about, in an ad agency, when\Na point like this is reached in a meeting...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.17,0:35:40.80,English,,0,0,0,,there's always some character\Nready with an idea, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:42.84,English,,0,0,0,,And it kills me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.93,0:35:44.43,English,,0,0,0,,It's the weirdest thing in the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.51,0:35:47.85,English,,0,0,0,,the way they sometimes precede their idea\Nwith a little phrase, see, like...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.93,0:35:50.85,English,,0,0,0,,Some account exec will get up,\Nand he'll say, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.94,0:35:52.77,English,,0,0,0,,"Okay, here's an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.85,0:35:56.48,English,,0,0,0,,Let's, uh, run it up the flagpole\Nand see if anyone salutes it."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.57,0:35:59.69,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's idiotic, but it's funny, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.78,0:36:04.28,English,,0,0,0,,I, uh\N- I got a little excited back there. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.28,0:36:07.03,English,,0,0,0,,didn't mean to get nasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.91,0:36:11.71,English,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you're not one of those\Nlets these emotional appeals influence him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.87,0:36:15.13,English,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.39,0:36:31.10,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's the matter with that fan.\NCan't seem to get it to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.48,0:36:35.02,English,,0,0,0,,♪ Be, be, be ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.11,0:36:37.19,English,,0,0,0,,♪ Ba, ba, ba, ba, bum ♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.77,0:36:39.69,English,,0,0,0,,Eh!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.82,0:36:43.03,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, you a salesman?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.11,0:36:44.61,English,,0,0,0,,I'm an architect.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.45,0:36:46.78,English,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.87,0:36:49.12,English,,0,0,0,,You know what the soft sell is?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.04,0:36:53.96,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, you got it. Believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.63,0:36:57.33,English,,0,0,0,,I got a different technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.13,0:36:59.92,English,,0,0,0,,Laughs, drinks, jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.01,0:37:02.26,English,,0,0,0,,Tricks. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.09,0:37:04.30,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.76,0:37:07.97,English,,0,0,0,,"Hit 'em where they live."\NThat's my motto.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.39,0:37:12.14,English,,0,0,0,,I made 27 grand last year\Nsellin' marmalade.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.98,0:37:15.48,English,,0,0,0,,That's not bad. I mean,\Nyou know, considering marmalade.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.69,0:37:20.48,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you\Ngettin' outta this - kicks?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.65,0:37:25.24,English,,0,0,0,,Or did somebody bump you on the head\None time and you haven't gotten over it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.32,0:37:27.03,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.03,0:37:30.58,English,,0,0,0,,You know, you do-gooders are all alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.66,0:37:33.33,English,,0,0,0,,You're always blowing your stacks\Nover some guy that fanned.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.42,0:37:38.25,English,,0,0,0,,But what are you wasting our time for?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.00,0:37:43.05,English,,0,0,0,,Why don't you donate five dollars to the\Ncause, and maybe it'll make you feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.34,0:37:48.59,English,,0,0,0,,This kid is guilty, pal.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.68,0:37:51.10,English,,0,0,0,,It's as plain as the nose on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.18,0:37:53.43,English,,0,0,0,,So why don't we stop\Nwasting our time here?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.52,0:37:56.44,English,,0,0,0,,We're gonna all get sore throats\Nif we keep it up, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.52,0:37:58.81,English,,0,0,0,,What difference does it make\Nif you get it here or at the ball game?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.86,0:38:02.78,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, no difference, pal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.86,0:38:04.65,English,,0,0,0,,No difference at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.58,0:38:18.46,English,,0,0,0,,Nice bunch of guys, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.54,0:38:20.83,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're about the same\Nas anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.92,0:38:23.71,English,,0,0,0,,Phew! Boy, what a murderous day.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.71,0:38:26.76,English,,0,0,0,,You think we'll be much longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.84,0:38:28.47,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.55,0:38:30.47,English,,0,0,0,,Aw, he's guilty for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.55,0:38:32.10,English,,0,0,0,,Not a doubt in the whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.18,0:38:34.72,English,,0,0,0,,We should -\NShould've been done already.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.98,0:38:38.23,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't mind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.31,0:38:40.73,English,,0,0,0,,Hmm. Beats workin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.40,0:38:45.57,English,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.95,0:38:50.03,English,,0,0,0,,You think he's not guilty, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.12,0:38:51.95,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.70,0:38:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know you, but I'm bettin'\Nyou never been wronger in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.58,0:38:59.00,English,,0,0,0,,You're wasting your time.\NYou ought to wrap it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.08,0:39:01.25,English,,0,0,0,,Supposing you were the one\Nwho was on trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.09,0:39:03.96,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not used to supposing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.05,0:39:08.55,English,,0,0,0,,I'm just a workingman.\NMy boss does the supposing. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.63,0:39:10.13,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll try one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.34,0:39:17.02,English,,0,0,0,,Supposing you talk us all out of this, and,\Nuh, the kid really did knife his father. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.94,0:39:27.23,English,,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.32,0:39:28.53,English,,0,0,0,,Hup.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.61,0:39:29.53,English,,0,0,0,,That one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.61,0:39:31.28,English,,0,0,0,,Sorry, blue eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.20,0:39:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,- Well, where else -\N- Okay, fellas, let's take our seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.70,0:39:37.62,English,,0,0,0,,Looks like we'll be here\Nfor dinner, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.70,0:39:40.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, now let's -\NLet's get down to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.17,0:39:41.54,English,,0,0,0,,Now, who wants to start it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.62,0:39:43.04,English,,0,0,0,,- I would.\N- Okay, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.13,0:39:45.21,English,,0,0,0,,You down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.30,0:39:49.17,English,,0,0,0,,The old man who lived downstairs says he\Nheard the kid yell out, "I'm gonna kill ya."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.26,0:39:51.88,English,,0,0,0,,A second later,\Nhe heard the body hit the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.97,0:39:55.85,English,,0,0,0,,Now, he ran to the door and he saw the kid\Nrunning down the stairs and out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.93,0:39:57.31,English,,0,0,0,,What does that mean to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.39,0:40:00.77,English,,0,0,0,,I was wondering how clearly the old man could\Nhave heard the boy's voice through the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.85,0:40:02.90,English,,0,0,0,,He didn't hear it through the ceiling.\NThe window was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.98,0:40:04.81,English,,0,0,0,,So was the one upstairs.\NIt was a hot night, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.90,0:40:06.23,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it was another apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.32,0:40:08.90,English,,0,0,0,,It's not that easy to identify a voice,\Nparticularly a shouting voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.99,0:40:10.57,English,,0,0,0,,- He identified it in court.\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.65,0:40:12.11,English,,0,0,0,,And don't forget the lady\Nacross the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.20,0:40:14.99,English,,0,0,0,,She looked right in the open window\Nand saw the boy stab his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.08,0:40:17.53,English,,0,0,0,,- Now, I mean, isn't that enough for you?\N- No, it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.62,0:40:19.58,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, how do you like this guy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.66,0:40:21.50,English,,0,0,0,,It's like talking into a dead phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.58,0:40:24.75,English,,0,0,0,,She said she saw the killing through the\Nwindows of a moving elevated train.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.83,0:40:28.34,English,,0,0,0,,There were six cars on the train.\NShe saw the killing through the last two cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.42,0:40:30.26,English,,0,0,0,,She remembered\Nthe most insignificant details.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.34,0:40:32.38,English,,0,0,0,,I don't see how you can argue with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.47,0:40:37.01,English,,0,0,0,,Has anybody here any idea\Nhow long it would take an el...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.69,0:40:47.27,English,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.36,0:40:48.86,English,,0,0,0,,This isn't a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.15,0:40:55.41,English,,0,0,0,,- Did you see him?\N- Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.49,0:40:57.24,English,,0,0,0,,- The nerve.\N- All right, listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.33,0:41:00.58,English,,0,0,0,,- The absolute nerve.\N- Forget it. It's not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.66,0:41:02.62,English,,0,0,0,,- "This isn't a game"?\N- Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.71,0:41:06.04,English,,0,0,0,,- Who does he think he is?\N- I'm telling you, forget it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.13,0:41:09.46,English,,0,0,0,,Has anybody any idea how long\Nit takes an elevated train...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.55,0:41:11.38,English,,0,0,0,,going at medium speed\Nto pass a given point?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.46,0:41:13.34,English,,0,0,0,,- What has that to do with anything?\N- How long? Take a guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.42,0:41:16.09,English,,0,0,0,,- I wouldn't have the slightest idea.\N- What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.18,0:41:18.05,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Maybe 10, 12 seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.06,0:41:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,I think that's a pretty good guess.\NAnyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.81,0:41:23.60,English,,0,0,0,,- That sounds right to me.\N- Come on. What's the guessing game for?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.69,0:41:25.52,English,,0,0,0,,- What do you say?\N- Ten seconds is about right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.60,0:41:27.52,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Say 10 seconds.\NWhat are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.61,0:41:32.65,English,,0,0,0,,This. It takes a six-car el train\N10 seconds to pass a given point.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.74,0:41:36.99,English,,0,0,0,,Now let's say the given point is the open window\Nof the room where the killing took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.07,0:41:40.37,English,,0,0,0,,You can reach out of that window\Nand almost touch the el tracks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.45,0:41:41.95,English,,0,0,0,,Now let me ask you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.04,0:41:44.29,English,,0,0,0,,Has anyone here\Never lived near the el tracks?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.37,0:41:48.00,English,,0,0,0,,Well, uh, I just finished painting an\Napartment that overlooked an el line.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.08,0:41:49.75,English,,0,0,0,,- I was there for three days.\N- What was it like?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.84,0:41:51.00,English,,0,0,0,,- What do you mean?\N- Noisy?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.09,0:41:53.63,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, brother. Don't matter though.\NWe were all punchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.72,0:41:56.30,English,,0,0,0,,I lived in a second-floor apartment\Nnear the el line once.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.38,0:41:59.43,English,,0,0,0,,When the window was open and the train\Ngoes by, the noise is almost unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.55,0:42:02.35,English,,0,0,0,,- You can hardly hear yourself think.\N- All right, you can't hear yourself think.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.43,0:42:04.85,English,,0,0,0,,- Will you get to the point?\N- I will. Now just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.93,0:42:08.56,English,,0,0,0,,Let's take two pieces of testimony\Nand try to put them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.65,0:42:12.73,English,,0,0,0,,First. The old man in the\Napartment downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.82,0:42:15.40,English,,0,0,0,,He says he heard the boy say\N"I'm gonna kill you"...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.49,0:42:18.24,English,,0,0,0,,and a split second later\Nheard a body hit the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.32,0:42:19.91,English,,0,0,0,,- One second later, right?\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.99,0:42:26.00,English,,0,0,0,,Second. The woman across the street swore\Npositively she looked out of the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.08,0:42:29.42,English,,0,0,0,,and saw the killing through the last two\Ncars of the passing elevated train, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.50,0:42:31.84,English,,0,0,0,,- The last two cars.\N- What are you giving us here?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.92,0:42:33.25,English,,0,0,0,,Now, just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.34,0:42:37.76,English,,0,0,0,,We've agreed that it takes 10 seconds\Nfor a train to pass a given point.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.59,0:42:41.93,English,,0,0,0,,Since the woman saw the killing\Nthrough the last two cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.01,0:42:46.98,English,,0,0,0,,we can assume that the body\Nhit the floor just as the train went by.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.06,0:42:51.52,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the train had been roaring\Nby the old man's window...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.61,0:42:55.11,English,,0,0,0,,a full 10 seconds\Nbefore the body hit the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.19,0:42:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,The old man,\Naccording to his own testimony...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.49,0:43:00.41,English,,0,0,0,,"I'm gonna kill you," body hitting\Nthe floor a split second later...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.49,0:43:02.95,English,,0,0,0,,would have had to hear the boy\Nmake this statement...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.03,0:43:04.91,English,,0,0,0,,with the el roaring past his nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.99,0:43:06.54,English,,0,0,0,,It's not possible he could've heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.62,0:43:08.79,English,,0,0,0,,- That's idiotic. Of course he heard it.\N- Do you think he could've heard it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.87,0:43:11.25,English,,0,0,0,,He said he yelled at the top of his voice.\NThat's good enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.33,0:43:13.59,English,,0,0,0,,Even if he heard something, he still\Ncouldn't have identified the voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.67,0:43:14.80,English,,0,0,0,,With the el roaring by?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.88,0:43:17.26,English,,0,0,0,,You're talking about a matter of seconds!\NNobody can be that accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.34,0:43:21.97,English,,0,0,0,,I think testimony that could put a boy into\Nthe electric chair should be that accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.18,0:43:26.10,English,,0,0,0,,You know something?\NI don't think he could've heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.18,0:43:28.52,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe he didn't hear it.\NI mean, with all that el noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.60,0:43:30.48,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, what are you people talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.56,0:43:32.60,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it stands to reason\Nhe couldn't have heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.69,0:43:34.61,English,,0,0,0,,Why should he lie?\NWhat's he got to gain?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.69,0:43:36.90,English,,0,0,0,,Attention maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.99,0:43:38.90,English,,0,0,0,,You keep coming in\Nwith these bright sayings!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.99,0:43:42.03,English,,0,0,0,,Why don't you send 'em in to a paper?\NThey pay three dollars apiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.12,0:43:44.32,English,,0,0,0,,What are you talking to him\Nlike that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.29,0:43:48.70,English,,0,0,0,,Guy talks like that to an old man\Nreally ought to get stepped on, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.79,0:43:50.62,English,,0,0,0,,You ought to have more respect, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.83,0:43:56.21,English,,0,0,0,,If you say stuff like that to him again,\NI'm gonna lay you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.18,0:44:09.14,English,,0,0,0,,Now you go ahead.\NYou - You say anything you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.23,0:44:13.27,English,,0,0,0,,Why do you think\Nthe old man might lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.35,0:44:16.77,English,,0,0,0,,It was just that I looked at him\Nfor a very long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.40,0:44:20.65,English,,0,0,0,,The seams of his jacket was split,\Nunder the shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.74,0:44:22.32,English,,0,0,0,,Or did you notice that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.41,0:44:24.91,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, to come to court like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.99,0:44:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.79,0:44:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,He was a very old man\Nin a torn jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.75,0:44:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,And he walked very slowly\Nto the stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.38,0:44:39.42,English,,0,0,0,,He was dragging his left leg\Nand trying to hide it...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.51,0:44:41.17,English,,0,0,0,,because he was ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.30,0:44:45.72,English,,0,0,0,,I think I know this man\Nbetter than anyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.60,0:44:52.02,English,,0,0,0,,This is a quiet, frightened,\Ninsignificant old man who...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.10,0:44:54.48,English,,0,0,0,,who has been nothing all his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.56,0:44:56.98,English,,0,0,0,,who has never had recognition...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.07,0:44:59.15,English,,0,0,0,,or his name in the newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.82,0:45:02.03,English,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.11,0:45:04.15,English,,0,0,0,,Nobody quotes him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.24,0:45:08.20,English,,0,0,0,,Nobody seeks his advice after 75 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.04,0:45:12.91,English,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, that's a very sad thing -\Nto be nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.62,0:45:17.96,English,,0,0,0,,A man like this needs to be quoted,\Nto be listened to.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.59,0:45:20.55,English,,0,0,0,,To be quoted just once.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.63,0:45:22.51,English,,0,0,0,,Very important to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.01,0:45:25.43,English,,0,0,0,,It would be so hard for him\Nto recede into the background...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.51,0:45:27.22,English,,0,0,0,,- Wait a minute.\N- When there was a chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.30,0:45:30.18,English,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to do - tell us he'd\Nlie just so he could be important once?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.26,0:45:32.89,English,,0,0,0,,No. He wouldn't really lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.98,0:45:36.44,English,,0,0,0,,But perhaps he made himself believe\Nhe heard those words...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.52,0:45:38.73,English,,0,0,0,,and recognized the boy's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.82,0:45:41.11,English,,0,0,0,,That's the most fantastic story\NI've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.19,0:45:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,How can you make up a thing like that?\NWhat do you know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.29,0:45:55.33,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh, does anybody\Nwant a cough drop?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.42,0:45:57.67,English,,0,0,0,,- No, thanks.\N- I'll take one.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.75,0:46:01.25,English,,0,0,0,,You can say what you like. I still don't\Nsee how anybody can think he's not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.34,0:46:03.84,English,,0,0,0,,There's something else\NI'd like to talk about for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.92,0:46:05.55,English,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.63,0:46:08.93,English,,0,0,0,,I think we've proved that the old man couldn't\Nhave heard the boy say "I'm gonna kill you."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.01,0:46:10.60,English,,0,0,0,,- But supposing -\N- You didn't prove it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.68,0:46:13.47,English,,0,0,0,,- What are you talking about?\N- Supposing he really did hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.56,0:46:15.98,English,,0,0,0,,This phrase, how many times\Nhave all of us used it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.06,0:46:17.56,English,,0,0,0,,Probably thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.65,0:46:19.27,English,,0,0,0,,"I could kill you for that, darling."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.36,0:46:21.27,English,,0,0,0,,"Junior, you do that once more,\Nand I'm gonna kill you."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.36,0:46:22.65,English,,0,0,0,,"Get in there, Rocky, and kill him."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.73,0:46:24.61,English,,0,0,0,,We say it every day. That doesn't mean\Nwe're really gonna kill anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.69,0:46:26.49,English,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.\NWhat are you trying to give us here?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.57,0:46:30.28,English,,0,0,0,,The phrase was "I'm gonna kill you."\NThe kid yelled it at the top of his lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.37,0:46:31.70,English,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me he didn't mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.78,0:46:34.08,English,,0,0,0,,Anybody says a thing like that\Nthe way he said it, they mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.16,0:46:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,Well, gee, now I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.71,0:46:40.42,English,,0,0,0,,I remember I was arguing with a guy I work\Nnext to at the bank a couple weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.50,0:46:42.25,English,,0,0,0,,He called me an idiot, so I yelled at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.34,0:46:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,Now listen! This guy's trying to make you\Nbelieve things that aren't so.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.38,0:46:47.47,English,,0,0,0,,The kid said he was gonna kill him,\Nand he did kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.55,0:46:50.51,English,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you this. Do you really think the\Nboy would shout out a thing like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.60,0:46:52.39,English,,0,0,0,,so the whole neighborhood could hear him?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.47,0:46:54.31,English,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.\NHe's much too bright for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.39,0:46:59.14,English,,0,0,0,,Bright? He's a common ignorant slob.\NHe don't even speak good English.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.23,0:47:02.06,English,,0,0,0,,"He doesn't even speak good English."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.53,0:47:08.32,English,,0,0,0,,Mr. Foreman, I'd like\Nto change my vote to not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.40,0:47:09.82,English,,0,0,0,,You what?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.91,0:47:12.32,English,,0,0,0,,- You heard me.\N- Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.24,0:47:14.66,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.74,0:47:17.20,English,,0,0,0,,The vote is nine to three,\Nfavor of guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.29,0:47:20.08,English,,0,0,0,,Well, if this isn't the living end. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.13,0:47:26.88,English,,0,0,0,,What are you basing it on -\Nthe stories this guy made up?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.51,0:47:29.84,English,,0,0,0,,You ought to write for one of those\Nkooky detective magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.93,0:47:31.76,English,,0,0,0,,You'd make a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.84,0:47:35.26,English,,0,0,0,,For crying out loud. The kid's own lawyer\Nknew he didn't stand a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.77,0:47:37.35,English,,0,0,0,,Right from the beginning,\Nhis own lawyer knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.43,0:47:39.23,English,,0,0,0,,You could see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.31,0:47:42.90,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, oh, boy. I'm tellin' you,\Nthis guy here is really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.73,0:47:45.52,English,,0,0,0,,Look, the kid had a lawyer, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.61,0:47:48.44,English,,0,0,0,,He presented his case, not you.\NHow come you got so much to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.53,0:47:51.36,English,,0,0,0,,- Look, lawyers aren't infallible, you know.\N- Baltimore, please. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.45,0:47:53.16,English,,0,0,0,,He was court-appointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.24,0:47:55.08,English,,0,0,0,,- What's that supposed to mean?\N- It could mean a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.16,0:47:58.41,English,,0,0,0,,It could mean he didn't want the case,\Nor he resented being appointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.50,0:48:00.33,English,,0,0,0,,It's the kind of case\Nthat brings him nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.41,0:48:03.38,English,,0,0,0,,no money, no glory,\Nnot even much chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.46,0:48:06.38,English,,0,0,0,,That's not a very promising situation\Nfor a young lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.46,0:48:09.38,English,,0,0,0,,He'd really have to believe in his client\Nto put up any kind of a good case...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.47,0:48:11.47,English,,0,0,0,,and, as you pointed out a minute ago,\Nobviously he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.55,0:48:14.39,English,,0,0,0,,Of course he didn't. Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.47,0:48:16.76,English,,0,0,0,,Who the heck could?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.85,0:48:19.77,English,,0,0,0,,Except maybe\Nsome guy's mother or somebody. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.85,0:48:22.10,English,,0,0,0,,Ah, look.\NWill you look at the time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.19,0:48:24.73,English,,0,0,0,,- Come on. For crying out -\N- Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.81,0:48:27.15,English,,0,0,0,,- I have made some notes here -\N- Notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.23,0:48:29.86,English,,0,0,0,,And I would like to -\Nplease, to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.94,0:48:32.20,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.\N- I have been listening very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.28,0:48:36.70,English,,0,0,0,,And, uh, it seems to me that this man\Nhas some very good points to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.78,0:48:41.41,English,,0,0,0,,From what was presented at the trial,\Nthe boy looks guilty on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.50,0:48:45.58,English,,0,0,0,,- But maybe if we go deeper?\N- Oh, come on, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.67,0:48:47.96,English,,0,0,0,,There is a question I would like to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.05,0:48:51.34,English,,0,0,0,,Let us assume that the boy\Nreally did commit the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.42,0:48:54.76,English,,0,0,0,,Now, this happened\Nat 10 minutes after 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.84,0:48:57.30,English,,0,0,0,,Now, how was he caught by the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.39,0:49:01.89,English,,0,0,0,,He came back home, uh, at 3:00 or so...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.98,0:49:05.73,English,,0,0,0,,and he was captured by two detectives\Nin the hallway of his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.81,0:49:10.40,English,,0,0,0,,Now, my question is,\Nif he really had killed his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.48,0:49:13.70,English,,0,0,0,,why would he come back home\Nthree hours later?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.78,0:49:16.66,English,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't he be afraid of being caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.74,0:49:18.49,English,,0,0,0,,He came home to get his knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.58,0:49:21.12,English,,0,0,0,,It's not nice to go around leaving knives\Nsticking in people's chests.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.20,0:49:23.96,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, especially relatives.\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.04,0:49:26.29,English,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything funny about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.38,0:49:29.92,English,,0,0,0,,The boy knew the knife could be identified\Nas the one he had just bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.00,0:49:32.17,English,,0,0,0,,He had to get it before the police did.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.26,0:49:36.72,English,,0,0,0,,But if he knew the knife could be identified,\Nwhy did he leave it there in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.26,0:49:40.14,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I think we can assume\Nthe boy ran out in a state of panic...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.22,0:49:42.60,English,,0,0,0,,after having just killed his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.68,0:49:45.64,English,,0,0,0,,When he finally calmed down,\Nhe realized he had left his knife there.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.73,0:49:48.65,English,,0,0,0,,Ah. This then depends\Non your definition of panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.73,0:49:51.11,English,,0,0,0,,He would have had to be\Ncalm enough to see to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.19,0:49:53.78,English,,0,0,0,,that there were no fingerprints\Nleft on the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.86,0:49:57.91,English,,0,0,0,,Now, where did this panic start\Nand where did it end?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.99,0:50:00.37,English,,0,0,0,,Look, you voted guilty.\NWhat side are ya on?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.45,0:50:04.00,English,,0,0,0,,I don't believe I have to be loyal\Nto one side or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.08,0:50:05.87,English,,0,0,0,,I'm simply asking questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.96,0:50:08.96,English,,0,0,0,,Well, this is just off the top of my head,\Nbut, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.04,0:50:11.54,English,,0,0,0,,well, if I were the boy\Nand I'd done the stabbing and everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.63,0:50:13.76,English,,0,0,0,,I'd take a chance\Nand go back for the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.84,0:50:16.34,English,,0,0,0,,I'll bet he figured that nobody\Nhad seen him running out...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.43,0:50:18.93,English,,0,0,0,,and that the body wouldn't be discovered\Ntill the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.01,0:50:21.05,English,,0,0,0,,Well, after all,\Nit was the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.14,0:50:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,I'll bet he'd figured nobody\Nwould find the body till the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.72,0:50:25.73,English,,0,0,0,,Pardon. This is my whole point.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.81,0:50:29.52,English,,0,0,0,,The woman across the street testified that\Nthe moment after she saw the killing...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.61,0:50:32.19,English,,0,0,0,,that is, a moment\Nafter the train went by...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.27,0:50:35.28,English,,0,0,0,,she screamed\Nand then went to telephone the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.36,0:50:38.74,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the boy certainly\Nmust have heard the scream...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.82,0:50:42.33,English,,0,0,0,,so he knew\Nthat somebody saw something.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.41,0:50:45.20,English,,0,0,0,,I just don't think\Nthat he would have gone back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.29,0:50:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,Two things. One, in his state of panic,\Nhe may not have heard the scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.12,0:50:49.79,English,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it wasn't very loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.88,0:50:53.25,English,,0,0,0,,Two, if he did hear it, he may not\Nhave connected it with his own act.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.34,0:50:56.38,English,,0,0,0,,Remember, he lived in a neighborhood\Nwhere screams were fairly commonplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.47,0:50:58.93,English,,0,0,0,,- There's your answer.\N- Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.01,0:51:01.89,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe the boy did kill his father,\Ndidn't hear the scream...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.97,0:51:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,did run out in a panic,\Ndid calm down three hours later...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.77,0:51:08.39,English,,0,0,0,,and come back to get the knife,\Nrisking being caught by the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.48,0:51:11.40,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe all of those things happened,\Nbut maybe they didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.48,0:51:14.23,English,,0,0,0,,I think there's enough doubt that we can\Nwonder whether he was there at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.32,0:51:15.98,English,,0,0,0,,during the time the killing took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.07,0:51:17.82,English,,0,0,0,,What do you mean doubt?\NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.90,0:51:19.61,English,,0,0,0,,Didn't the old man see him\Nrunning out of the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.70,0:51:21.49,English,,0,0,0,,He's twisting the facts, I'm telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.57,0:51:24.91,English,,0,0,0,,Did or didn't the old man see the kid\Nrunning out of the house at 12:10?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.99,0:51:26.91,English,,0,0,0,,Well, did or didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.00,0:51:30.21,English,,0,0,0,,- He says he did.\N- "Says he did"? Boy! How do you like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.29,0:51:33.25,English,,0,0,0,,- Now, look, witnesses can make mistakes.\N- Sure, when you want them to, they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.34,0:51:35.59,English,,0,0,0,,Or when he wants them to, they do.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.67,0:51:37.51,English,,0,0,0,,- Keep the yelling down!\N- Oh, you keep saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.59,0:51:39.30,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe what we need\Nis a little yelling in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.38,0:51:41.09,English,,0,0,0,,These guys\Nkeep going off every which way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.18,0:51:43.09,English,,0,0,0,,Did hear the scream.\NDidn't hear the scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.18,0:51:46.35,English,,0,0,0,,What difference does it make? You people\Nare talking only about the little details.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.43,0:51:48.93,English,,0,0,0,,You're forgetting the important stuff.\NI mean, all of a sudden, everybody here...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.02,0:51:51.39,English,,0,0,0,,- I want to call for another vote.\N- I'm talking here!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.48,0:51:55.15,English,,0,0,0,,There's another vote called for.\NNow let's take our seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.03,0:52:01.57,English,,0,0,0,,I never saw so much time\Nspent on nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.66,0:52:03.36,English,,0,0,0,,It only takes a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.45,0:52:07.87,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. I guess the fastest way\Nis to find out who's voting not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.95,0:52:10.71,English,,0,0,0,,Now, all those voting not guilty,\Nplease raise your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.96,0:52:15.54,English,,0,0,0,,Still the same.\NOne, two, three not guilty. Nine guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.63,0:52:17.30,English,,0,0,0,,So, now where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.38,0:52:20.80,English,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, we can yackety-yack until\Nnext Tuesday. Where's it all getting us?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.88,0:52:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,Pardon. I vote not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.72,0:52:26.72,English,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.81,0:52:30.10,English,,0,0,0,,What are ya talking about? I mean,\Nwe're all going crazy in here or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.18,0:52:33.98,English,,0,0,0,,The kid is guilty.\NWhy don't you listen to the facts?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.06,0:52:36.31,English,,0,0,0,,Tell him, will ya?\NNow this is getting to be a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.40,0:52:39.61,English,,0,0,0,,The vote is eight to four,\Nfavor of guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.69,0:52:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,What is this, love your underprivileged\Nbrother week or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.45,0:52:45.95,English,,0,0,0,,I want you to get up and tell me\Nwhy you changed your vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.03,0:52:50.33,English,,0,0,0,,- Come on. Give me your reasons.\N- I don't have to defend my decision to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.41,0:52:52.16,English,,0,0,0,,There is a reasonable doubt in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.25,0:52:55.25,English,,0,0,0,,What reasonable doubt? That's nothing but words.\NHere, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.33,0:53:00.26,English,,0,0,0,,The kid you just decided isn't guilty\Nwas seen ramming this into his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.34,0:53:02.34,English,,0,0,0,,Now, what about this,\NMr. Reasonable Doubt?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.42,0:53:05.09,English,,0,0,0,,That's not the knife.\NDon't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.18,0:53:07.35,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.43,0:53:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,I'm telling ya, this is the craziest.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.81,0:53:11.98,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, what are we supposed to believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.06,0:53:14.89,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, you're sittin' here, you're pulling\Nstories out of thin air, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.98,0:53:18.69,English,,0,0,0,,A guy like this, if he's, uh, sitting\Nringside at the Dempsey-Firpo fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.77,0:53:21.23,English,,0,0,0,,he'd be trying to tell you that, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.32,0:53:23.70,English,,0,0,0,,Look. Now, what about the old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.78,0:53:26.36,English,,0,0,0,,Are we supposed to believe that he\Ndidn't get up and run to his door...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.45,0:53:29.45,English,,0,0,0,,and see the kid tearing down the steps\N15 seconds after the killing?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.54,0:53:32.00,English,,0,0,0,,He's just saying so to be important, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.08,0:53:34.87,English,,0,0,0,,- I mean, what's the point of the whole thing?\N- Wait. Hold it a second, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.96,0:53:37.17,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, and the Baltimore rooter\Nis heard from again now...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.25,0:53:39.21,English,,0,0,0,,and pop-ups are fallin' for base hits\Nwherever we look.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.30,0:53:42.55,English,,0,0,0,,Hold it a second. Now, look -\NDid the old man say he ran to the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.63,0:53:45.59,English,,0,0,0,,Ran, walked. What's the difference? He got on, didn't he?\NI mean, he got there, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.68,0:53:48.22,English,,0,0,0,,- No, now wait a second.\N- He said he ran. At least I think he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.30,0:53:51.72,English,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't remember what he said, but I\Ndon't see how he could have run to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.81,0:53:54.18,English,,0,0,0,,Ηe said he went\Nfrom his bedroom to the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.27,0:53:55.89,English,,0,0,0,,- Now, isn't that enough?\N- Where was the bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.98,0:53:58.23,English,,0,0,0,,- It was down the hall somewhere.\N- I thought you remembered everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.31,0:54:00.57,English,,0,0,0,,- Don't you remember that?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.65,0:54:02.86,English,,0,0,0,,Mr. Foreman, I'd like to see\Na diagram of the apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.99,0:54:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,- Why don't we just have 'em run the trial all over again\Nso you can get everything straight? - Mr. Foreman.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.28,0:54:08.91,English,,0,0,0,,How come you're the only one in this room\Nwants to see exhibits all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.99,0:54:11.70,English,,0,0,0,,- I want to see this one too.\N- And I'd like to stop wasting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.79,0:54:14.62,English,,0,0,0,,If we're gonna start wading through all that\Nnonsense about where the body was found...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.71,0:54:16.66,English,,0,0,0,,We're not,\Nnot unless somebody else wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.75,0:54:18.46,English,,0,0,0,,But I'd like to find out if an old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.54,0:54:20.92,English,,0,0,0,,who drags one foot when he walks\N'cause he had a stroke last year...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.00,0:54:23.42,English,,0,0,0,,can get from his bedroom\Nto his front door in 15 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.51,0:54:25.17,English,,0,0,0,,- He said 20 seconds.\N- Ηe said 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.26,0:54:27.43,English,,0,0,0,,He said 20 seconds.\NWhat are you trying to distort...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.51,0:54:30.76,English,,0,0,0,,- He said 15.\N- How does he know how long 15 seconds is?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.85,0:54:32.51,English,,0,0,0,,You can't judge a thing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.60,0:54:34.97,English,,0,0,0,,- He said 15 seconds.\N- He was very positive about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.06,0:54:37.27,English,,0,0,0,,He was an old man.\NHalf the time he was confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.35,0:54:39.65,English,,0,0,0,,How could he be positive about anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.32,0:54:51.45,English,,0,0,0,,I don't see what you're going to prove here.\NThe man said he saw the boy running out.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.53,0:54:53.70,English,,0,0,0,,Well, let's see\Nif the details bear him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.79,0:54:56.66,English,,0,0,0,,As soon as the body hit the floor,\Nhe said he heard footsteps upstairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.75,0:54:58.41,English,,0,0,0,,running toward the front door...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.50,0:55:01.58,English,,0,0,0,,heard the upstairs door open,\Nthe footsteps start down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.67,0:55:03.80,English,,0,0,0,,He said he got to his own front door\Nas fast as he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.88,0:55:05.96,English,,0,0,0,,and he swore it couldn't have been\Nmore than 15 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.05,0:55:07.72,English,,0,0,0,,Now, if the killer\Nbegan running immediately...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.80,0:55:10.01,English,,0,0,0,,- Maybe he didn't.\N- The old man said he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.09,0:55:12.80,English,,0,0,0,,You ought to be at Atlantic City\Nat that hairsplitters convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.10,0:55:16.22,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, why don't you stop makin'\Nsmart remarks all the time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.31,0:55:19.44,English,,0,0,0,,My friend, for your three dollars a day,\Nyou have to listen to everything, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.52,0:55:21.23,English,,0,0,0,,Now that you've got that thing in here,\Nwhat about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.31,0:55:23.48,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Here's the apartment\Nwhere the killing took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.57,0:55:26.61,English,,0,0,0,,The old man's apartment\Nwas directly beneath and exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.69,0:55:29.90,English,,0,0,0,,Here are the el tracks, the bedroom,\Nliving room, kitchen, bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.99,0:55:31.99,English,,0,0,0,,Here's the hall. Here are the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.07,0:55:34.33,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the old man\Nwas in this bedroom right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.41,0:55:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,He says he crossed to the door\Nand walked down the hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.16,0:55:40.12,English,,0,0,0,,opened the front door just in time\Nto see the boy running down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.21,0:55:43.54,English,,0,0,0,,- Am I right so far?\N- That's the story, for the 19th time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.63,0:55:47.17,English,,0,0,0,,- Fifteen seconds after the body hit the floor.\N- Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.26,0:55:49.30,English,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see. It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.38,0:55:53.39,English,,0,0,0,,It's 12 feet from the bed to the door.\NThe hall is 43 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.47,0:55:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,He would have had to walk 12 feet,\Nopen the bedroom door...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.77,0:56:00.39,English,,0,0,0,,walk 43 feet down and open the front door\Nall in 15 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.48,0:56:03.19,English,,0,0,0,,- Do you think he could have done it?\N- Sure he could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.27,0:56:05.86,English,,0,0,0,,He can walk only very slowly.\NThey had to help him into the witness chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.94,0:56:07.61,English,,0,0,0,,You make it sound like a long walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.69,0:56:10.03,English,,0,0,0,,For an old man who had a stroke,\Nit is a long walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.11,0:56:13.53,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh! What are you doing?\N- I'm gonna try it, see how long it took him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.66,0:56:16.99,English,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, you want to try it?\NWhy didn't his lawyer bring it up if it's so important?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.12,0:56:20.75,English,,0,0,0,,- Maybe he just didn't think about it, huh?\N- What do you mean, didn't think of it? You think the man's an idiot or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.83,0:56:22.37,English,,0,0,0,,- It's an obvious thing.\N- Did you think of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.46,0:56:24.13,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, smart guy.\NDon't matter whether I thought of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.21,0:56:26.42,English,,0,0,0,,He didn't bring it up because he knew it would\Nhurt his case. What do you think of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.55,0:56:30.38,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe he didn't bring it up because it would have\Nmeant bullying and badgering a helpless old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.47,0:56:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,You know that doesn't sit very well with a jury.\NMost lawyers avoid it if they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.89,0:56:36.60,English,,0,0,0,,- So, what kind of a bum is he then?\N- That's what I've been asking, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.68,0:56:39.72,English,,0,0,0,,Pass me that chair, will you?\NThose two chairs are the old man's bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.81,0:56:42.69,English,,0,0,0,,I just paced off 12 feet across the room.\NThis will be the bedroom door.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.77,0:56:45.40,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's crazy.\NYou can't recreate a thing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.48,0:56:47.69,English,,0,0,0,,- I'd like to see it.\N- The hall was 43 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.78,0:56:49.78,English,,0,0,0,,I'll pace from that wall and back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.07,0:56:54.91,English,,0,0,0,,Look, this is absolutely insane.\NWhat are you wasting everybody's time in here for?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.99,0:56:57.87,English,,0,0,0,,According to you, it'll only take 15 seconds.\NNow, we can spare that, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.83,0:57:03.50,English,,0,0,0,,Come on. Knock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.58,0:57:05.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.17,0:57:07.21,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay, killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.29,0:57:08.88,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.22,0:57:13.26,English,,0,0,0,,Will you stand right there\Nand mark the front door?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.34,0:57:15.84,English,,0,0,0,,It was chain-locked according\Nto the testimony, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.93,0:57:18.10,English,,0,0,0,,- Has anybody got a watch with a second hand?\N- I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.18,0:57:20.60,English,,0,0,0,,When you want me to start, stamp your foot.\NThat'll be the body falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.68,0:57:22.60,English,,0,0,0,,You can time me from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.68,0:57:24.77,English,,0,0,0,,What are we gonna do, play charades now?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.85,0:57:26.90,English,,0,0,0,,- Come on! What are we waiting for?\N- Okay, I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.98,0:57:28.90,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I want to wait\Ntill the second hand reaches 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.98,0:57:30.90,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.62,0:57:40.62,English,,0,0,0,,Come on. Speed it up.\NHe could walk twice as fast as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.08,0:57:44.54,English,,0,0,0,,You want me to walk faster than that,\NI will.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.43,0:58:03.89,English,,0,0,0,,Lock. Door. Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.98,0:58:05.98,English,,0,0,0,,- Right.\N- What's the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.06,0:58:09.31,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, exactly 41 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.40,0:58:11.65,English,,0,0,0,,This is what I think happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.73,0:58:14.57,English,,0,0,0,,The old man heard the fight between the boy\Nand his father a few hours earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.65,0:58:17.49,English,,0,0,0,,Then when he's lying in bed, he heard the\Nbody hit the floor in the boy's apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.57,0:58:21.08,English,,0,0,0,,heard the woman scream from across the street,\Ngot to his front door as fast as he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.16,0:58:23.74,English,,0,0,0,,heard somebody racing down the stairs\Nand assumed it was the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.83,0:58:25.66,English,,0,0,0,,- I think that's possible.\N- Assumed?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.75,0:58:28.25,English,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.33,0:58:34.30,English,,0,0,0,,Brother, I've seen all kinds of dishonesty in\Nmy day, but this little display takes the cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.38,0:58:39.09,English,,0,0,0,,You all come in here with your hearts bleeding all\Nover the floor about slum kids and injustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.18,0:58:41.18,English,,0,0,0,,You listen to some fairy tales.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.26,0:58:43.56,English,,0,0,0,,Suddenly you start getting through\Nto some of these old ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.64,0:58:46.60,English,,0,0,0,,Well, you're not getting through to me.\NI've had enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.69,0:58:48.73,English,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.81,0:58:51.52,English,,0,0,0,,You all know he's guilty!\NHe's got to burn!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.61,0:58:53.40,English,,0,0,0,,You're letting him slip\Nthrough our fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.48,0:58:55.69,English,,0,0,0,,"Slip through our fingers"?\NAre you his executioner?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.78,0:58:57.45,English,,0,0,0,,I'm one of 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.61,0:59:00.45,English,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you'd like to pull the switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.53,0:59:02.53,English,,0,0,0,,For this kid, you bet I would.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.62,0:59:05.87,English,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for you. What it must\Nfeel like to want to pull the switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.75,0:59:10.67,English,,0,0,0,,Ever since you walked into this room, you've been\Nacting like a self-appointed public avenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.75,0:59:15.05,English,,0,0,0,,You want to see this boy die because you\Npersonally want it, not because of the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.13,0:59:17.30,English,,0,0,0,,- You're a sadist.\N- You...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.38,0:59:21.22,English,,0,0,0,,Let me go!\NI'll kill him. I'll kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.30,0:59:23.72,English,,0,0,0,,You don't really mean\Nyou'll kill me, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.02,0:59:33.36,English,,0,0,0,,Is there anything wrong, gentlemen?\NI heard some noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.44,0:59:37.44,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. Everything's all right. We're just\N- You know, friendly little argument. It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.53,0:59:40.82,English,,0,0,0,,Um, listen, we're through with that diagram.\NYou can take it if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.20,0:59:43.87,English,,0,0,0,,Here you are. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.41,0:59:51.50,English,,0,0,0,,What are you lookin' at?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.27,1:00:14.31,English,,0,0,0,,I suppose somebody\Nhas to start it off again.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.40,1:00:18.11,English,,0,0,0,,- I beg pardon.\N- "I beg pardon." What are you so polite about?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.19,1:00:20.28,English,,0,0,0,,For the same reason you're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.36,1:00:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,It's the way I was brought up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.28,1:00:26.20,English,,0,0,0,,This fighting...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.29,1:00:28.33,English,,0,0,0,,That's not why we are here, to fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.41,1:00:30.79,English,,0,0,0,,We have a responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.96,1:00:36.54,English,,0,0,0,,This, I have always thought,\Nis a remarkable thing about democracy...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.63,1:00:38.50,English,,0,0,0,,that we are...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.72,1:00:42.30,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, what is the word?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.38,1:00:45.47,English,,0,0,0,,Notified.\NThat we are notified by mail...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.55,1:00:49.89,English,,0,0,0,,to come down to this place\Nto decide on the guilt or innocence...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.98,1:00:54.02,English,,0,0,0,,of a man we have never heard of before.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.10,1:00:58.65,English,,0,0,0,,We have nothing to gain or lose\Nby - by our verdict.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.57,1:01:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,This is one of the reasons\Nwhy we are strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.99,1:01:06.82,English,,0,0,0,,We should not make it a personal thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.16,1:01:09.83,English,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.04,1:01:13.33,English,,0,0,0,,If nobody else has an idea,\NI may have a cutie here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.42,1:01:16.17,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, I haven't given it much thought,\Nbut let's throw it out on the stoop...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.25,1:01:17.88,English,,0,0,0,,and see if the cat licks it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.96,1:01:20.30,English,,0,0,0,,- The cat licks it up?\N- Yeah. If the boy...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.80,1:01:26.93,English,,0,0,0,,Look how dark it's getting out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.01,1:01:29.47,English,,0,0,0,,I'll bet we're gonna have a storm now.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.27,1:01:33.73,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, oh, boy. It's really hot, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.23,1:01:38.02,English,,0,0,0,,Pardon me, but don't you ever sweat?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.44,1:01:41.61,English,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.69,1:01:43.69,English,,0,0,0,,Well, listen. I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.78,1:01:46.95,English,,0,0,0,,I was wondering if, uh, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.03,1:01:49.33,English,,0,0,0,,maybe we should take another vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.41,1:01:53.70,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, great. Maybe we can follow this one up\Nwith a little dancing and refreshments, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.79,1:01:55.58,English,,0,0,0,,- Hmm.\N- Mr. Foreman?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.38,1:01:59.92,English,,0,0,0,,Well, that's okay with me.\NAnyone doesn't want to vote?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.00,1:02:03.21,English,,0,0,0,,- Hey, come on. Come on.\N- I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.30,1:02:06.80,English,,0,0,0,,I think we ought to have an open ballot -\Ncall out our votes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.89,1:02:09.10,English,,0,0,0,,Let's see who stands where.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.18,1:02:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,That sounds fair to me.\NAnyone object?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.43,1:02:17.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'll call off your jury numbers.\NOne.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.15,1:02:20.94,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's me. I vote guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.02,1:02:22.82,English,,0,0,0,,Two?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.90,1:02:24.40,English,,0,0,0,,Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.95,1:02:27.78,English,,0,0,0,,- Number three?\N- Guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.78,1:02:30.32,English,,0,0,0,,Number four?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.83,1:02:33.62,English,,0,0,0,,Guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.70,1:02:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,- Number five?\N- Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.54,1:02:40.84,English,,0,0,0,,- Number six?\N- Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.84,1:02:43.50,English,,0,0,0,,Number seven?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.59,1:02:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,Guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.38,1:02:47.43,English,,0,0,0,,Number eight?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.51,1:02:49.18,English,,0,0,0,,Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.51,1:02:53.43,English,,0,0,0,,- Number nine?\N- Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.52,1:02:55.68,English,,0,0,0,,- Number 10?\N- Guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.48,1:02:59.52,English,,0,0,0,,Number 11?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.60,1:03:01.44,English,,0,0,0,,Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.52,1:03:03.02,English,,0,0,0,,Number 12?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.94,1:03:06.28,English,,0,0,0,,Number 12.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.36,1:03:07.86,English,,0,0,0,,Guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.79,1:03:15.87,English,,0,0,0,,The vote is now six to six.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.95,1:03:19.12,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NAnd we go into extra innings here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.54,1:03:26.05,English,,0,0,0,,Six to six. I'm telling you, some of you\Npeople in here must be out of your minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.13,1:03:27.97,English,,0,0,0,,A kid like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.05,1:03:31.30,English,,0,0,0,,I don't think the kind of boy he is\Nhas anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.39,1:03:33.47,English,,0,0,0,,The facts are supposed\Nto determine the case.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.56,1:03:35.72,English,,0,0,0,,Don't give me that!\NI'm sick and tired of facts!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.81,1:03:37.81,English,,0,0,0,,You can twist them any way you like.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.89,1:03:40.48,English,,0,0,0,,That's exactly the point\Nthis gentleman has been making.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.56,1:03:43.48,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh!\N- I mean, you keep shouting at the top of your lungs.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.15,1:03:47.07,English,,0,0,0,,I'd like to be a few years younger.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.15,1:03:49.07,English,,0,0,0,,That man gets on my...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.45,1:03:55.28,English,,0,0,0,,- My, it's hot in here, isn't it?\N- Do you want a drink of water?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.37,1:03:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,No. No, thanks. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.92,1:04:08.71,English,,0,0,0,,It's gonna rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.80,1:04:11.05,English,,0,0,0,,Well, how'd you figure that out, killer?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.30,1:04:14.18,English,,0,0,0,,How come you changed your vote?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.26,1:04:16.68,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it just seemed to me\Nthere was room for doubt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.77,1:04:18.97,English,,0,0,0,,You haven't got a leg to stand on.\NYou know that, I hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.06,1:04:22.06,English,,0,0,0,,I don't feel that way.\NThere were a lot of details that never came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.15,1:04:25.69,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. Well, good luck.\N- Oh, come on. You're like everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.77,1:04:27.98,English,,0,0,0,,You think too much.\NYou get mixed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.24,1:04:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,- You know what I mean?\N- Now, listen. I don't think you have any right...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.28,1:04:35.87,English,,0,0,0,,Loudmouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.59,1:05:31.09,English,,0,0,0,,Look at that come down, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.26,1:05:34.13,English,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.22,1:05:36.72,English,,0,0,0,,this reminds me of a storm we had last...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.80,1:05:40.26,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, when was that? November...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.35,1:05:43.43,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Something.\NIt was quite a storm we had there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.52,1:05:45.89,English,,0,0,0,,It was right in the middle of a game.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.98,1:05:48.61,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, we were behind 7-6...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.69,1:05:51.28,English,,0,0,0,,but we just started to move the ball,\Nright off the tackle.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.36,1:05:54.15,English,,0,0,0,,Started cutting right -\Nslash here and slash right in...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.24,1:05:56.03,English,,0,0,0,,cut right through.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.11,1:05:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,And, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.70,1:06:00.91,English,,0,0,0,,We had this kid Slattery, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.08,1:06:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,A real - He was an ox.\NYou know, a real ox.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.54,1:06:08.04,English,,0,0,0,,I wish I had another one just like him.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.13,1:06:12.63,English,,0,0,0,,I forgot to tell you. I'm the assistant head\Ncoach at the Andrew J. McCorkle High School.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.71,1:06:14.80,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh, yeah?\N- That's out in Queens.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.88,1:06:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,And, uh, anyway...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.72,1:06:19.80,English,,0,0,0,,we're starting to move along real nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.89,1:06:23.06,English,,0,0,0,,Their whole line is just -\Nthey're just coming apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.35,1:06:28.10,English,,0,0,0,,And it starts to come down\Ncats and dogs, just like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.19,1:06:30.81,English,,0,0,0,,Just whoosh - you know, right down.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.11,1:06:35.49,English,,0,0,0,,Well, that was murder, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.57,1:06:38.16,English,,0,0,0,,I swear, I - I nearly bawled.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.24,1:06:40.57,English,,0,0,0,,You just - You couldn't go nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.83,1:06:43.16,English,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.80,1:07:01.30,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, what is it with this fan here?\NHow come...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.06,1:07:10.81,English,,0,0,0,,Hey! Ηuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.90,1:07:14.19,English,,0,0,0,,Must have been\Non the same switch with the lights.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.19,1:07:18.36,English,,0,0,0,,Well, things are looking up here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.03,1:07:20.53,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.37,1:07:27.37,English,,0,0,0,,Boy. That's better.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.05,1:07:35.55,English,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.63,1:07:37.30,English,,0,0,0,,Two points.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.30,1:07:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,Any of you guys ever go to the Garden?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.60,1:07:48.48,English,,0,0,0,,That's a damn stupid thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.56,1:07:50.73,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry. I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.77,1:07:53.15,English,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.86,1:07:56.36,English,,0,0,0,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.44,1:07:59.78,English,,0,0,0,,Well, how do you like it?\NEven Steven.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.86,1:08:02.24,English,,0,0,0,,Pretty surprising, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.32,1:08:03.82,English,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.62,1:08:09.12,English,,0,0,0,,Say, that business before,\Nwhen that tall guy - what's-his-name...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.21,1:08:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,was trying to bait me -\NThat doesn't prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.00,1:08:14.59,English,,0,0,0,,I'm a pretty excitable person.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.67,1:08:18.51,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, where does he come off calling me\Na public avenger, sadist and everything?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.59,1:08:22.09,English,,0,0,0,,Anyone in his right mind\Nwould blow his stack, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.18,1:08:24.47,English,,0,0,0,,He was just trying to bait me.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.55,1:08:26.56,English,,0,0,0,,He did an excellent job.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.35,1:08:31.56,English,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what I think.\NWe're going nowhere here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.64,1:08:34.19,English,,0,0,0,,I'm ready to walk into court right now\Nand declare a hung jury.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.27,1:08:36.11,English,,0,0,0,,There's no point in this thing\Ngoing on any more.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.19,1:08:37.52,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I go for that too.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.61,1:08:40.44,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, let's take it in to the judge and let\Nthe kid take his chances with 12 other guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.53,1:08:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,I don't think the judge will accept a hung jury.\NWe haven't been in here very long.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.45,1:08:45.12,English,,0,0,0,,Well, let's find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.20,1:08:46.91,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not in favor of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.99,1:08:50.20,English,,0,0,0,,Listen. This kid wouldn't stand a chance\Nwith another jury, and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.29,1:08:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,Come on! We're hung. Nobody's gonna\Nchange his vote. Let's take it inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.21,1:08:55.42,English,,0,0,0,,You still don't think there's room\Nfor reasonable doubt?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.50,1:08:56.79,English,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.88,1:08:58.17,English,,0,0,0,,Pardon.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.25,1:09:01.51,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe you don't fully understand\Nthe term "reasonable doubt."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.59,1:09:04.13,English,,0,0,0,,What do you mean I don't understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.22,1:09:07.18,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, how do ya like this guy?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.26,1:09:08.93,English,,0,0,0,,I'm tellin' ya, they're all alike.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.02,1:09:11.85,English,,0,0,0,,They come over here, running for their life,\Nand before they can take a deep breath...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.94,1:09:14.31,English,,0,0,0,,they're telling us how\Nto run the show, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.40,1:09:16.19,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, the arrogance of this guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.27,1:09:20.86,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, all right. Let's stop\Nthe arguing for about two minutes in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.94,1:09:23.32,English,,0,0,0,,Now, who's got something\Nconstructive to say?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.40,1:09:26.95,English,,0,0,0,,I'd like to go over something,\Nif you gentlemen don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.03,1:09:29.70,English,,0,0,0,,An important point for the prosecution\Nwas the fact...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.79,1:09:32.54,English,,0,0,0,,that after the boy claimed\Nhe'd been at the movies...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.62,1:09:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,during the hours\Nthat the killing took place...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.71,1:09:38.59,English,,0,0,0,,couldn't remember the names of the movies\Nor the stars who appeared in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.67,1:09:41.17,English,,0,0,0,,This gentleman here has put up that point\Nin here several times.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.26,1:09:42.71,English,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.80,1:09:44.68,English,,0,0,0,,It was the only alibi the boy offered...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.76,1:09:47.26,English,,0,0,0,,and he himself couldn't back it up\Nwith any details at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.35,1:09:50.60,English,,0,0,0,,Putting yourself in the boy's place,\Ndo you think you could remember details...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.68,1:09:54.14,English,,0,0,0,,after an upsetting experience such as\Nbeing slapped in the face by your father?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.23,1:09:57.44,English,,0,0,0,,I think so, if there were\Nany special details to remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.52,1:10:00.69,English,,0,0,0,,The boy couldn't remember the names of the movies\Nhe saw because be wasn't there that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.78,1:10:02.82,English,,0,0,0,,According to\Nthe police testimony in court...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.90,1:10:06.03,English,,0,0,0,,the boy was questioned by the detectives\Nin the kitchen of his apartment...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.11,1:10:09.03,English,,0,0,0,,while the body of his father\Nwas lying on the floor in the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.12,1:10:11.70,English,,0,0,0,,Do you think you could remember details\Nunder those circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.79,1:10:13.79,English,,0,0,0,,- I do.\N- Under great emotional stress?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.87,1:10:16.37,English,,0,0,0,,- Under great emotional stress.\N- He remembered them correctly in court.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.46,1:10:18.42,English,,0,0,0,,He named the pictures\Nand the stars who played in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.50,1:10:21.67,English,,0,0,0,,Yes. His lawyer took great pains\Nto bring that out.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.75,1:10:24.30,English,,0,0,0,,He had three months from the night\Nof the murder to the day of the trial...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.38,1:10:26.01,English,,0,0,0,,in which to memorize them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.09,1:10:28.76,English,,0,0,0,,It's not difficult for a lawyer to find out\Nwhat played at a particular theater...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.85,1:10:30.51,English,,0,0,0,,on a particular night.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.60,1:10:34.22,English,,0,0,0,,I'll take the testimony of the policemen who\Ninterrogated the boy right after the murder...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.31,1:10:36.73,English,,0,0,0,,when he couldn't remember\Na thing about the movies...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.81,1:10:38.73,English,,0,0,0,,great emotional stress or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.81,1:10:42.11,English,,0,0,0,,- I'd like to ask you a personal question.\N- Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.19,1:10:45.44,English,,0,0,0,,- Where were you last night?\N- I was home.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.53,1:10:48.07,English,,0,0,0,,- How about the night before that?\N- Come on! What is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.16,1:10:49.49,English,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.57,1:10:52.12,English,,0,0,0,,I left the office at 8:30\Nand went straight home and to bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.20,1:10:53.87,English,,0,0,0,,And the night before that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.95,1:10:56.37,English,,0,0,0,,That was, uh, Tuesday night?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.46,1:10:58.46,English,,0,0,0,,The night of the bridge tournament.\NI played bridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.54,1:10:59.88,English,,0,0,0,,Monday night?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.96,1:11:03.17,English,,0,0,0,,When you get down\Nto New Year's Eve, 1954, let me know, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.17,1:11:07.13,English,,0,0,0,,Monday night?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.38,1:11:11.39,English,,0,0,0,,Monday night, uh,\Nmy wife and I went to the movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.47,1:11:13.10,English,,0,0,0,,- What did you see?\N- The Scarlet Circle.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.18,1:11:16.43,English,,0,0,0,,- It was a clever whodunit.\N- What was the second feature?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.52,1:11:19.14,English,,0,0,0,,The, um...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.23,1:11:21.90,English,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you in a minute. The, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.98,1:11:26.15,English,,0,0,0,,Remarkable Mrs., uh, something...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.24,1:11:28.70,English,,0,0,0,,The...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.78,1:11:31.45,English,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Bainbridge.\NThe Remarkable Mrs. Bainbridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.53,1:11:34.28,English,,0,0,0,,I saw that.\NIt's called The Amazing Mrs. Bainbridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.58,1:11:37.96,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes. The Amazing Mrs. Bainbridge.\NI think that's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.04,1:11:40.54,English,,0,0,0,,Who was in The Amazing Mrs. Bainbridge?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.63,1:11:44.29,English,,0,0,0,,Barbara... Long, I think it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.38,1:11:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,A dark, very pretty girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.72,1:11:50.22,English,,0,0,0,,Ling or Long - something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.30,1:11:53.51,English,,0,0,0,,- Who else?\N- I'd never heard of them before.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.60,1:11:58.02,English,,0,0,0,,It was a very inexpensive second feature\Nwith, uh, unknown...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.10,1:12:01.23,English,,0,0,0,,And you weren't under\Nan emotional stress, were you?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.15,1:12:06.27,English,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.36,1:12:08.03,English,,0,0,0,,I wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.90,1:12:11.66,English,,0,0,0,,I think the point is made.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.74,1:12:14.49,English,,0,0,0,,Big point!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.58,1:12:16.74,English,,0,0,0,,You can talk till your tongue\Nis draggin' on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.83,1:12:20.91,English,,0,0,0,,The boy is guilty, period.\NYou know what I mean, my friend?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.00,1:12:24.25,English,,0,0,0,,- Who's got those cough drops?\N- They're all gone, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.25,1:12:28.51,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy. Look at that rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.59,1:12:30.97,English,,0,0,0,,There goes your ball game.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.05,1:12:33.47,English,,0,0,0,,It's only a shower.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.55,1:12:35.72,English,,0,0,0,,Besides, they got the infield covered.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.81,1:12:38.97,English,,0,0,0,,Right. Say, could I see that knife\Na second, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.77,1:12:44.10,English,,0,0,0,,Well, we're still tied up six to six.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.19,1:12:46.19,English,,0,0,0,,Who's got a suggestion?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.27,1:12:48.28,English,,0,0,0,,It's five after 6:00.\NLet's get some dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.36,1:12:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,Why don't we wait till 7:00,\Ngive it another hour, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.90,1:12:53.03,English,,0,0,0,,Okay with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.11,1:12:55.28,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, there's something I'd like to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.37,1:12:58.91,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's been bothering me a little,\Nand as long as we're stuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.00,1:13:02.87,English,,0,0,0,,Well, there was this whole business\Nabout the stab wound and how it was made...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.96,1:13:04.58,English,,0,0,0,,the downward angle of it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.67,1:13:06.67,English,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me we're gonna\Nstart with that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.75,1:13:08.38,English,,0,0,0,,They've been over it and over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.46,1:13:10.76,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I know they did,\Nbut I don't go along with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.84,1:13:14.84,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the boy was 5 feet 7 inches tall.\NHis father was 6'2...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.93,1:13:17.10,English,,0,0,0,,That's a difference of seven inches.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.18,1:13:19.85,English,,0,0,0,,It's a very awkward thing to stab down\Ninto the chest of someone...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.93,1:13:21.93,English,,0,0,0,,who's more than half a foot\Ntaller than you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.02,1:13:24.14,English,,0,0,0,,Give me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.23,1:13:27.02,English,,0,0,0,,I'll give you a demonstration.\NSomebody get up.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.40,1:13:30.32,English,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.82,1:13:37.53,English,,0,0,0,,I want you to watch this 'cause\NI don't want to have to do it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.62,1:13:40.37,English,,0,0,0,,I'll make myself about six\Nor seven inches shorter, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.45,1:13:43.58,English,,0,0,0,,- It's about right. Maybe a little more.\N- Okay. A little more.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.38,1:13:53.80,English,,0,0,0,,That's not funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.89,1:13:59.72,English,,0,0,0,,Now, nobody's hurt. Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.39,1:14:02.18,English,,0,0,0,,Right. Nobody hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.65,1:14:10.44,English,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the way I'd stab a man\Nwho was taller than I was.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.53,1:14:12.98,English,,0,0,0,,Look at the angle - down and in.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.07,1:14:15.15,English,,0,0,0,,And this is the way it was done.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.24,1:14:17.41,English,,0,0,0,,Now tell me I'm wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.62,1:14:23.04,English,,0,0,0,,- Down and in. I guess there's no argument.\N- Hold it a minute, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.12,1:14:24.96,English,,0,0,0,,Can you give me that?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.96,1:14:27.87,English,,0,0,0,,Boy, I hate these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.96,1:14:29.63,English,,0,0,0,,- Did you ever see a knife fight?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.71,1:14:31.29,English,,0,0,0,,- You?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.38,1:14:34.17,English,,0,0,0,,Anybody here ever see a knife fight?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.26,1:14:37.05,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I have.\NYou know, on my back stoop...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.14,1:14:39.47,English,,0,0,0,,the lot across the street, backyard.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.55,1:14:41.97,English,,0,0,0,,Switchblades came\Nwith the neighborhood where I lived.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.06,1:14:45.31,English,,0,0,0,,It's funny I never thought of it before.\NI guess you try to forget those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.39,1:14:48.77,English,,0,0,0,,- How do you use a switchblade?\N- Well, you'd never use it like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.52,1:14:52.82,English,,0,0,0,,See, you use too much time\Nswitching hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.57,1:14:57.07,English,,0,0,0,,Here's how - underhanded.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.78,1:15:02.83,English,,0,0,0,,Anyone who's ever used a switch knife\Nwouldn't handle it any other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.91,1:15:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,- Are you sure?\N- I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.62,1:15:07.46,English,,0,0,0,,That's why they're made to open like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.54,1:15:10.17,English,,0,0,0,,- You'd say the boy was pretty handy with a knife?\N- Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.25,1:15:13.42,English,,0,0,0,,You think he could have made\Nthe kind of wound that killed his father?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.50,1:15:17.42,English,,0,0,0,,No. Not with the experience he'd had\Nall his life handling these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.51,1:15:19.51,English,,0,0,0,,I feel he'd have gone for him underhanded.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.59,1:15:22.64,English,,0,0,0,,How do you know? Were you\Nin the room when the father was killed?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.72,1:15:24.72,English,,0,0,0,,No. Neither was anybody else.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.81,1:15:28.02,English,,0,0,0,,So what are you giving us all this\Nmumbo jumbo for? I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.10,1:15:31.35,English,,0,0,0,,I don't think you can determine what type of\Nwound the boy might or might not have made...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.44,1:15:34.07,English,,0,0,0,,simply because he knew\Nhow to handle a knife.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.15,1:15:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.57,1:15:38.65,English,,0,0,0,,- I don't know.\N- What do you mean you don't know?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.74,1:15:40.57,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.79,1:15:46.79,English,,0,0,0,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.87,1:15:50.62,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know about the rest of them, but I'm getting a\Nlittle tired of this yackety-yackin' back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.71,1:15:54.17,English,,0,0,0,,It's gettin' us nowhere.\NSo I guess I'll have to break it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.25,1:15:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,I change my vote to not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.88,1:16:00.22,English,,0,0,0,,- You what?\N- You heard me. I've had enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.30,1:16:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,What do you mean you've had enough?\NThat's no answer!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.85,1:16:06.81,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, listen. You just take care\Nof yourself, huh? You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.89,1:16:10.85,English,,0,0,0,,He's right. That's not an answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.94,1:16:13.90,English,,0,0,0,,What kind of a man are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.98,1:16:17.11,English,,0,0,0,,You have sat here and voted guilty\Nwith everyone else...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.19,1:16:21.45,English,,0,0,0,,because there are some baseball tickets\Nburning a hole in your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.53,1:16:25.78,English,,0,0,0,,And now you've changed your vote because you\Nsay you're sick of all the talking here?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.79,1:16:28.25,English,,0,0,0,,Now listen, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.33,1:16:33.00,English,,0,0,0,,Who tells you that you have the right\Nto play like this with a man's life?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.08,1:16:35.59,English,,0,0,0,,- Don't you care -\N- Now wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.67,1:16:39.67,English,,0,0,0,,- You can't talk like that to me!\N- I can talk like that to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.76,1:16:41.63,English,,0,0,0,,If you want to vote not guilty...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.72,1:16:44.09,English,,0,0,0,,then do it because you are convinced\Nthe man is not guilty...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.18,1:16:45.97,English,,0,0,0,,not because you've had enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.06,1:16:48.64,English,,0,0,0,,And if you think he is guilty,\Nthen vote that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.72,1:16:51.94,English,,0,0,0,,Or don't you have the guts\Nto do what you think is right?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.02,1:16:54.27,English,,0,0,0,,- Now listen.\N- Guilty or not guilty?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.06,1:16:58.65,English,,0,0,0,,- I told you, not guilty.\N- Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.32,1:17:01.95,English,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't have to...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.03,1:17:05.16,English,,0,0,0,,You do have to! Say it! Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.24,1:17:07.70,English,,0,0,0,,All right. I don't, uh, think he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.21,1:17:18.84,English,,0,0,0,,I want another vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.92,1:17:21.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. There's another vote called for.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.51,1:17:24.38,English,,0,0,0,,I guess the quickest way is a show of hands.\NAnyone object?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.47,1:17:27.39,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. All those voting not guilty,\Nraise your hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.31,1:17:33.48,English,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four,\Nfive, six, seven...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.31,1:17:37.98,English,,0,0,0,,eight.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.90,1:17:44.03,English,,0,0,0,,Um, nine.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.03,1:17:50.04,English,,0,0,0,,Um, all those voting guilty,\Nraise your hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.12,1:17:52.50,English,,0,0,0,,One, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.58,1:17:55.08,English,,0,0,0,,Well, the vote's nine to three\Nin favor of acquittal.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.08,1:17:58.25,English,,0,0,0,,I don't understand you people!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.34,1:18:00.50,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, all these picky little points\Nyou keep bringing up.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.59,1:18:03.92,English,,0,0,0,,They don't mean nothing!\NYou saw this kid just like I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.01,1:18:07.51,English,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna tell me you believe\Nthat phony story about losing the knife...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.60,1:18:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,and that business\Nabout being at the movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.68,1:18:12.68,English,,0,0,0,,Look, you know how these people lie.\NIt's born in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.77,1:18:14.81,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, what the heck.\NI don't have to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.89,1:18:16.85,English,,0,0,0,,They don't know what the truth is.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.94,1:18:20.65,English,,0,0,0,,And let me tell you, they don't need\Nany real big reason to kill someone either.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.73,1:18:22.48,English,,0,0,0,,No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.57,1:18:25.61,English,,0,0,0,,They get drunk!\NOh, they're real big drinkers, all of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.70,1:18:28.87,English,,0,0,0,,You know that.\NAnd bang - someone's lying in the gutter.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.95,1:18:31.95,English,,0,0,0,,Well, nobody's blaming them for it.\NThat's the way they are, by nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.04,1:18:34.12,English,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean? Violent!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.21,1:18:35.71,English,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.79,1:18:38.79,English,,0,0,0,,Ηuman life don't mean\Nas much to them as it does to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.79,1:18:42.80,English,,0,0,0,,Look! They're lushing it up\Nand fighting all the time...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.88,1:18:44.88,English,,0,0,0,,and if somebody gets killed,\Nso somebody gets killed!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.97,1:18:46.34,English,,0,0,0,,They don't care!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.43,1:18:48.64,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure, there's some good things\Nabout 'em too.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.72,1:18:50.68,English,,0,0,0,,Look, I'm the first one to say that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.76,1:18:54.06,English,,0,0,0,,I've known a couple who were okay, but\Nthat's the exception, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.14,1:18:57.89,English,,0,0,0,,Most of 'em, it's like they have no feelings.\NThey can do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.98,1:19:00.56,English,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.65,1:19:02.69,English,,0,0,0,,I'm - I'm trying to tell ya...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.78,1:19:04.78,English,,0,0,0,,you're making a big mistake, you people.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.86,1:19:07.86,English,,0,0,0,,This kid is a liar!\NI know it. I know all about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.57,1:19:11.74,English,,0,0,0,,Listen to me.\NThey're no good.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.83,1:19:14.16,English,,0,0,0,,There's not a one of 'em who's any good.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.21,1:19:18.67,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, what -\NWhat's happening in here?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.75,1:19:21.00,English,,0,0,0,,I'm speaking my piece, and you...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.21,1:19:23.88,English,,0,0,0,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.96,1:19:26.42,English,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.51,1:19:28.97,English,,0,0,0,,We're - This kid on trial here, his type...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.05,1:19:31.05,English,,0,0,0,,Well, don't you know about them?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.01,1:19:36.47,English,,0,0,0,,Th-There's - There's a danger here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.56,1:19:38.64,English,,0,0,0,,These people are dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.73,1:19:41.77,English,,0,0,0,,They're... wild.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.86,1:19:43.77,English,,0,0,0,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.86,1:19:46.19,English,,0,0,0,,- Listen.\N- I have.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.28,1:19:49.28,English,,0,0,0,,Now sit down\Nand don't open your mouth again.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.20,1:19:55.95,English,,0,0,0,,I was only trying to... tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.45,1:20:36.74,English,,0,0,0,,It's always difficult to keep personal\Nprejudice out of a thing like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.87,1:20:41.87,English,,0,0,0,,Wherever you run into it,\Nprejudice always obscures the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.46,1:20:45.84,English,,0,0,0,,I don't really know what the truth is.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.92,1:20:48.84,English,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose anybody\Nwill ever really know.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.13,1:20:54.09,English,,0,0,0,,Nine of us now seem to feel\Nthat the defendant is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.18,1:20:57.18,English,,0,0,0,,But we're just gambling on probabilities.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.26,1:20:59.22,English,,0,0,0,,We may be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.31,1:21:01.68,English,,0,0,0,,We may be trying to let\Na guilty man go free.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.77,1:21:03.23,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.31,1:21:05.31,English,,0,0,0,,Nobody really can.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.40,1:21:07.77,English,,0,0,0,,But we have a reasonable doubt...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.86,1:21:11.36,English,,0,0,0,,and that's something\Nthat's very valuable in our system.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.45,1:21:15.99,English,,0,0,0,,No jury can declare a man guilty\Nunless it's sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.45,1:21:19.83,English,,0,0,0,,We nine can't understand...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.91,1:21:22.62,English,,0,0,0,,how you three are still so sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.46,1:21:25.46,English,,0,0,0,,- Maybe you can tell us.\N- I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.84,1:21:30.34,English,,0,0,0,,You've made some excellent points, but I\Nstill believe the boy is guilty of murder...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.42,1:21:32.13,English,,0,0,0,,and I have two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.22,1:21:35.34,English,,0,0,0,,One, the evidence\Ngiven by the woman across the street...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.43,1:21:38.05,English,,0,0,0,,who actually saw the murder committed.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.14,1:21:40.72,English,,0,0,0,,As far as I'm concerned,\Nthat's the most important testimony.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.81,1:21:44.06,English,,0,0,0,,And two, the fact that she\Ndescribed the stabbing by saying...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.14,1:21:49.77,English,,0,0,0,,she saw the boy raise his arm over his head\Nand stab down into the father's chest.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.86,1:21:51.90,English,,0,0,0,,She saw him do it the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.99,1:21:53.90,English,,0,0,0,,That's absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.99,1:21:56.57,English,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about this woman for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.66,1:21:59.74,English,,0,0,0,,She said she went to bed\Nabout 11:00 that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.83,1:22:03.41,English,,0,0,0,,Her bed was next to the window,\Nand she could look out while lying down...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.50,1:22:07.58,English,,0,0,0,,and see directly into the boy's room\Nacross the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.67,1:22:10.30,English,,0,0,0,,She tossed and turned for over an hour,\Nunable to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.38,1:22:14.55,English,,0,0,0,,Finally, she turned toward the window\Nat about 10 minutes after 12:00...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.63,1:22:19.76,English,,0,0,0,,and, as she looked out, she saw the killing\Nthrough the windows of a passing el train.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.85,1:22:22.56,English,,0,0,0,,She said the lights went out\Nimmediately after the killing...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.64,1:22:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,but that she got a good look at the boy\Nin the act of stabbing his father.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.44,1:22:32.28,English,,0,0,0,,As far as I can see it,\Nthis is unshakable testimony.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.03,1:22:35.70,English,,0,0,0,,- Well, that's the whole case.\N- What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.08,1:22:42.74,English,,0,0,0,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.37,1:22:46.83,English,,0,0,0,,I-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.92,1:22:48.92,English,,0,0,0,,So much evidence to sift.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.00,1:22:50.96,English,,0,0,0,,This is a pretty complicated business.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.05,1:22:54.84,English,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I don't see\Nhow you can vote for acquittal.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.92,1:22:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,It's not so easy to arrange\Nall the evidence in order.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.34,1:22:59.39,English,,0,0,0,,You can throw out\Nall the other evidence!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.47,1:23:03.06,English,,0,0,0,,The woman saw him do it!\NWhat else do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.14,1:23:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, well, maybe -\N- Let's vote on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.10,1:23:07.27,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. There's another vote called for.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.35,1:23:09.19,English,,0,0,0,,Anybody object?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.27,1:23:12.32,English,,0,0,0,,All right. I'm changing my vote.\NHe's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.40,1:23:14.82,English,,0,0,0,,Anybody else?\NThe vote is eight to four.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.90,1:23:18.49,English,,0,0,0,,Why is this such a personal triumph\Nfor you - this one vote?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.57,1:23:22.03,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. I say we're a hung jury.\NI say we take it in to the judge.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.12,1:23:24.83,English,,0,0,0,,Ηow about it?\NI want to hear arguments.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.91,1:23:27.41,English,,0,0,0,,You, you're the leader of the cause.\NWhat about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.67,1:23:31.50,English,,0,0,0,,Let's go over it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.59,1:23:33.50,English,,0,0,0,,We've been over it again!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.59,1:23:38.38,English,,0,0,0,,The boy in the gray flannel suit here is bouncin'\Nbackwards and forwards like a tennis ball.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.47,1:23:42.30,English,,0,0,0,,No point in getting nasty\Nand trying to turn this into a contest.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.26,1:23:45.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.81,1:23:48.85,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe we can talk about\Nsetting some kind of time limit.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.94,1:23:51.06,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, once around for the deal, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.77,1:23:55.53,English,,0,0,0,,It's a quarter after 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.61,1:23:57.57,English,,0,0,0,,Someone before mentioned 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.65,1:24:00.03,English,,0,0,0,,I think that's a point at which\Nwe might begin to discuss...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.11,1:24:03.37,English,,0,0,0,,the question of whether\Nwe're a hung jury or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.45,1:24:05.12,English,,0,0,0,,Don't you feel well?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.45,1:24:08.41,English,,0,0,0,,I feel perfectly well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.50,1:24:11.21,English,,0,0,0,,I was saying that 7:00\Nwould be a reasonable time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.29,1:24:14.21,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, the reason I asked about that\Nwas because, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.29,1:24:15.88,English,,0,0,0,,you were rubbing your nose like...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.96,1:24:18.63,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry for interrupting...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.72,1:24:21.93,English,,0,0,0,,but you made a gesture\Nthat reminded me of something.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.01,1:24:24.05,English,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to settle something here.\NDo you mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.14,1:24:26.14,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I think this is important.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.22,1:24:29.02,English,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.10,1:24:31.73,English,,0,0,0,,Now then,\NI'm sure you'll pardon me for this...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.81,1:24:34.73,English,,0,0,0,,but I was wondering why\Nyou were rubbing your nose like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.82,1:24:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.57,1:24:40.74,English,,0,0,0,,At this point, I happen to be talking\Nto the gentleman sitting next to you!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.82,1:24:44.07,English,,0,0,0,,Now, why were you rubbing\Nyour nose like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.16,1:24:48.24,English,,0,0,0,,Well, if it's any of your business, I was\Nrubbing it because it bothers me a little.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.33,1:24:49.95,English,,0,0,0,,Oh. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.04,1:24:53.92,English,,0,0,0,,- Is it - Is it because of your eyeglasses?\N- It is.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.00,1:24:55.75,English,,0,0,0,,Now can we get on to something else?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.84,1:25:00.42,English,,0,0,0,,Your eyeglasses made those two\Ndeep impressions on the sides of your nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.51,1:25:02.68,English,,0,0,0,,I hadn't noticed that before.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.76,1:25:06.26,English,,0,0,0,,- That must be annoying.\N- It is very annoying.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.35,1:25:08.26,English,,0,0,0,,Well, I wouldn't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.35,1:25:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,I've never worn eyeglasses.\NTwenty-twenty.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.77,1:25:14.31,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, will you come on already\Nwith the optometrist bit?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.23,1:25:19.78,English,,0,0,0,,The woman who testified\Nthat she saw the killing...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.86,1:25:23.40,English,,0,0,0,,had those same marks\Non the sides of her nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.41,1:25:26.62,English,,0,0,0,,Holy smokes! You know, he's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.70,1:25:28.37,English,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.45,1:25:32.21,English,,0,0,0,,Just give me a minute,\Nand I'll be finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.29,1:25:35.12,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know if anyone else\Nnoticed that about her.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.21,1:25:39.09,English,,0,0,0,,I didn't think of it then,\Nbut I've been going over her face...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.13,1:25:42.26,English,,0,0,0,,in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.34,1:25:44.34,English,,0,0,0,,She had those same marks.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.34,1:25:49.51,English,,0,0,0,,- She kept rubbing them in court.\N- He's right. She did do that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.56,1:25:55.23,English,,0,0,0,,This woman was about, uh -\Nabout 45 years old.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.31,1:25:59.27,English,,0,0,0,,She was making a tremendous effort\Nto look 35...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.36,1:26:01.57,English,,0,0,0,,for her first public appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.65,1:26:04.90,English,,0,0,0,,Heavy makeup, dyed hair...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.99,1:26:08.87,English,,0,0,0,,brand-new clothes that should have\Nbeen worn by a younger woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.95,1:26:10.62,English,,0,0,0,,No glasses.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.70,1:26:12.37,English,,0,0,0,,No, women do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.45,1:26:14.87,English,,0,0,0,,See if you can get the\Nmental picture of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.96,1:26:16.79,English,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, no glasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.88,1:26:19.59,English,,0,0,0,,How do you know whether she wore glasses?\NJust 'cause she was rubbing her nose?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.67,1:26:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,Now, she had those marks. I saw 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.96,1:26:23.88,English,,0,0,0,,So what?\NWhat do ya think that means?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.97,1:26:27.18,English,,0,0,0,,- Listen, I'm getting so sick of your yelling in here!\N- Come on. Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.26,1:26:30.26,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, listen. Listen, he's right.\NI saw them too.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.35,1:26:33.47,English,,0,0,0,,I was the closest one to her. She had these,\Nuh - these things on the side of her nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.56,1:26:36.77,English,,0,0,0,,- What do you call those on the side?\N- Well, what point are you making here?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.85,1:26:40.73,English,,0,0,0,,She had dyed hair, marks on her nose.\NWell, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.82,1:26:45.11,English,,0,0,0,,Could those marks be made\Nby anything other than eyeglasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.70,1:26:51.03,English,,0,0,0,,No, they couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.12,1:26:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,I didn't see any marks!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.75,1:26:56.46,English,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.54,1:26:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,Strange, but I didn't\Nthink about it before.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.17,1:27:01.29,English,,0,0,0,,Well, what about the lawyer?\NWhy didn't he say something?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.38,1:27:04.30,English,,0,0,0,,There are 12 people in here\Nconcentrating on this case.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.38,1:27:06.47,English,,0,0,0,,Eleven of us didn't think of it either.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.55,1:27:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,Well, what about the district attorney?\NDo you think he'd pull a trick like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.80,1:27:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,Have her testify without her glasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.81,1:27:15.73,English,,0,0,0,,Did you ever see a woman who had to wear glasses and\Ndidn't want to because she thinks they spoil her looks?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.81,1:27:19.31,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. She had marks on her nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.40,1:27:23.07,English,,0,0,0,,I'm giving you that.\NFrom glasses, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.15,1:27:27.32,English,,0,0,0,,She didn't want to wear 'em out of the house\Nso people would think she's gorgeous.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.40,1:27:31.99,English,,0,0,0,,But when she saw this kid killing his\Nfather, she was in the house alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.08,1:27:34.29,English,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.37,1:27:38.37,English,,0,0,0,,- Do you wear glasses when you go to bed?\N- No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.08,1:27:42.00,English,,0,0,0,,No one wears eyeglasses to bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.09,1:27:45.09,English,,0,0,0,,It's logical to assume that she wasn't\Nwearing them when she was in bed...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.17,1:27:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,tossing and turning, trying to fall asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.01,1:27:49.34,English,,0,0,0,,- How do you know?\N- I don't know! I'm guessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.43,1:27:51.89,English,,0,0,0,,I'm also guessing that she probably\Ndidn't put her glasses on...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.97,1:27:54.10,English,,0,0,0,,when she turned\Nto look casually out of the window.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.18,1:27:56.93,English,,0,0,0,,And she herself testified the killing\Ntook place just as she looked out.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.02,1:28:00.06,English,,0,0,0,,The lights went off a split second later.\NShe couldn't have had time to put them on then.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.15,1:28:01.77,English,,0,0,0,,- Wait a second.\N- Here's another guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.86,1:28:05.94,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe she honestly thought she saw the boy\Nkill his father. I say she only saw a blur.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.03,1:28:09.61,English,,0,0,0,,How do you know what she saw?\NHow does he know all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.70,1:28:12.45,English,,0,0,0,,How do you know what kind of glasses she wore?\NMaybe they were sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.53,1:28:15.16,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe she was farsighted.\NWhat do you know about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.24,1:28:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,I only know the woman's eyesight\Nis in question now.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.58,1:28:24.71,English,,0,0,0,,She had to be able to identify a person\N60 feet away, at night, without glasses.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.80,1:28:27.17,English,,0,0,0,,You can't send someone off to die\Non evidence like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.26,1:28:29.26,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't give me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.34,1:28:31.51,English,,0,0,0,,Don't you think the woman\Nmight have made a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.59,1:28:34.01,English,,0,0,0,,- No.\N- It's not possible?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.10,1:28:35.72,English,,0,0,0,,No, it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.68,1:28:40.60,English,,0,0,0,,Is it possible?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.73,1:28:43.40,English,,0,0,0,,Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.57,1:28:50.24,English,,0,0,0,,Do you think he's guilty?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.32,1:28:52.32,English,,0,0,0,,I think he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.08,1:28:56.74,English,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.62,1:29:02.67,English,,0,0,0,,No. I'm convinced.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.75,1:29:04.33,English,,0,0,0,,Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.42,1:29:06.21,English,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.29,1:29:08.21,English,,0,0,0,,I have a reasonable doubt now.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.30,1:29:09.84,English,,0,0,0,,Eleven to one.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.92,1:29:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,Well, what about all the other evidence?\NWhat about all that stuff?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.93,1:29:15.01,English,,0,0,0,,The knife, the whole business!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.10,1:29:18.01,English,,0,0,0,,Well, you said we could throw out\Nall the other evidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.77,1:29:25.94,English,,0,0,0,,Well, what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.94,1:29:30.61,English,,0,0,0,,You're alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.69,1:29:34.53,English,,0,0,0,,I don't care whether I'm alone or not!\NIt's my right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.70,1:29:39.87,English,,0,0,0,,It's your right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.00,1:29:51.42,English,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you want?\NI say he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.05,1:29:56.39,English,,0,0,0,,- We want to hear your arguments.\N- I gave you my arguments.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.39,1:29:59.51,English,,0,0,0,,We're not convinced.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.60,1:30:02.39,English,,0,0,0,,We want to hear them again.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.48,1:30:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,We have as much time as it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.15,1:30:14.61,English,,0,0,0,,Everything - Every single thing\Nthat took place in that courtroom...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.70,1:30:16.61,English,,0,0,0,,but I mean everything -\Nsays he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.70,1:30:19.16,English,,0,0,0,,What do you think,\NI'm an idiot or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.83,1:30:22.91,English,,0,0,0,,Why don't you take that stuff\Nabout the old man?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.00,1:30:26.17,English,,0,0,0,,The old man who lived there\Nand heard everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.83,1:30:29.50,English,,0,0,0,,Or this business about the knife.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.59,1:30:31.59,English,,0,0,0,,What? 'Cause he found another one\Nexactly like it?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.67,1:30:35.01,English,,0,0,0,,The old man saw him\Nright there on the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.09,1:30:37.93,English,,0,0,0,,What's the difference\Nhow many seconds it was?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.10,1:30:41.10,English,,0,0,0,,Every single thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.52,1:30:45.68,English,,0,0,0,,The knife falling through\Na hole in his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.77,1:30:49.11,English,,0,0,0,,You can't prove he didn't get to the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.19,1:30:51.61,English,,0,0,0,,Sure, you can take all the time,\Nhobble around the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.69,1:30:54.28,English,,0,0,0,,But you can't prove it!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.20,1:30:59.82,English,,0,0,0,,And what about this business\Nof the el and the movies?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.91,1:31:02.95,English,,0,0,0,,There's a phony deal\Nif I ever heard one.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.04,1:31:07.25,English,,0,0,0,,I'll bet ya $5,000\NI'd remember the movies I saw.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.33,1:31:09.58,English,,0,0,0,,I'm telling ya,\Neverything that's gone on...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.67,1:31:13.50,English,,0,0,0,,has been twisted and turned!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.59,1:31:15.67,English,,0,0,0,,This business with the glasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.76,1:31:21.30,English,,0,0,0,,How do you know she didn't have them on?\NThis woman testified in open court!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.39,1:31:25.35,English,,0,0,0,,And what about hearing the kid yell, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.43,1:31:28.69,English,,0,0,0,,I'm telling ya, I've got\Nall the facts here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.86,1:31:31.73,English,,0,0,0,,Here. Ah...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.11,1:31:36.61,English,,0,0,0,,Well, that's it!\NThat's the whole case.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.83,1:31:45.41,English,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.71,1:31:49.71,English,,0,0,0,,Say something!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.84,1:31:58.42,English,,0,0,0,,You lousy bunch of bleeding hearts.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.09,1:32:01.01,English,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna intimidate me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.09,1:32:03.60,English,,0,0,0,,I'm entitled to my opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.98,1:32:11.27,English,,0,0,0,,Rotten kids.\NYou work your life out!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.11,1:32:18.07,English,,0,0,0,,I can't keep...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.74,1:32:24.41,English,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.29,1:32:30.12,English,,0,0,0,,Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.50,1:32:35.17,English,,0,0,0,,Not guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.17,1:32:39.80,English,,0,0,0,,Not...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.35,1:32:52.52,English,,0,0,0,,Um, we're ready now.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.18,1:34:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.18,1:34:53.85,English,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.93,1:34:55.43,English,,0,0,0,,Davis.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.52,1:34:57.44,English,,0,0,0,,My name's McCardle.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.77,1:35:01.44,English,,0,0,0,,Well, so long.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.52,1:35:03.03,English,,0,0,0,,So long.
